Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.63,0:01:07.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我長久以來的恐懼…\N{\rENG}I have long feared...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.51,0:01:13.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是我舊日的罪愆會回來糾纏我\N{\rENG}...that my sins would return to visit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.26,0:01:16.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,代價之高，我無法承受\N{\rENG}And the cost is more than I can bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.32,0:01:23.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,決戰　　  時刻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.12,0:01:46.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,山繆！信差來了！\N{\rENG}Samuel! A postrider!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.30,0:01:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“R” An "R."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.56,0:01:59.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.56,0:02:02.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個呢？\N{\rENG}What about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.26,0:02:43.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝　　不客氣\N{\rENG}- Thank you. - You're welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:28.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸…\N{\rENG}Father! Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.52,0:03:33.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,9磅，11盎司，好極了\N{\rENG}Nine pounds, eleven ounces. That's perfect. Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.03,0:03:35.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸，有信差！\N{\rENG}Father, a postrider!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:38.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,你南田的種子種好了嗎？\N{\rENG}Did you finish planting the field?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.66,0:03:39.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,種好一半多了\N{\rENG}More than half.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.91,0:03:43.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,偷偷去游泳，浪費了一些時間吧？\N{\rENG}Those swimming breaks really cut into the day, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.45,0:03:46.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴你了吧\N{\rENG}Told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.26,0:03:58.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯瑪斯\N{\rENG}Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.80,0:04:00.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,等爸爸\N{\rENG}Wait for Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.15,0:05:01.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起\N{\rENG}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:07.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,1776年，南卡羅萊納州{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.77,0:05:31.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,伊莉莎白·普頓·馬汀之墓 卒於1773年2月18日，享年35歲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:37.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就是了，北極星\N{\rENG}That's her. The North Star.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.40,0:05:39.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,看到了嗎？\N{\rENG}See?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.94,0:05:43.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要從北斗七星的最前面兩顆星開始看\N{\rENG}You start from the front two stars of the Big Dipper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.86,0:05:45.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後往上數\N{\rENG}And then you count up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.41,0:05:48.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,數到五指的寬度時…\N{\rENG}You count up five finger lengths...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.99,0:05:51.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在那兒了\N{\rENG}...and it's right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.00,0:05:55.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,它會一直俯視著我們\N{\rENG}And she'll always be looking down on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.17,0:05:59.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,永遠保護我們\N{\rENG}And protect us. Forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.30,0:06:02.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,來，睡覺了\N{\rENG}Come. Into bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.43,0:06:12.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安，晚安，梅格\N{\rENG}Good night. Good night, Meg.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:17.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓她知道媽在那兒會好得多\N{\rENG}It helps her to know Mother's there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:22.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安\N{\rENG}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.03,0:07:06.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,郵件裡有什麼？\N{\rENG}So what was in the mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:21.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,紐約州和賓夕法尼亞的議會…\N{\rENG}"The New York and Pennsylvania assemblies...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.34,0:07:23.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,在辯論獨立事宜\N{\rENG}...are debating independence."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.88,0:07:26.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,中部的殖民地呢？\N{\rENG}What about the middle colonies?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:31.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,在賈斯特城，他們燒毀了海關\N{\rENG}"In Chestertown, they burned the customs house...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:33.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,嚴懲了兩名官員\N{\rENG}...and tar and feathered two magistrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.22,0:07:36.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們被燒死\N{\rENG}They died of... They died of burns."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.73,0:07:38.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,真是蠢貨\N{\rENG}Damn fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.98,0:07:42.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是說誰？作者還是那兩個官員？\N{\rENG}Who? The writers or the magistrates?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:45.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,有沒談及大陸會議的事？\N{\rENG}What does it say about the Continental Congress?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.66,0:07:53.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,上面說會在七月宣佈獨立\N{\rENG}It says here they'll make a declaration of independence by July.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.64,0:08:12.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,彼德·庫本加入獨立軍了\N{\rENG}Peter Cuppin joined the Continentals.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.19,0:08:21.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,他才十七，比我還小一歲\N{\rENG}He's 17, a year younger than I.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:36.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,國民大會開會，我被叫到查理士城去了\N{\rENG}Well, the assembly's been convened, so I've been called to Charles Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.41,0:08:38.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要去查理士城？　對\N{\rENG}- We're going to Charles Town? - We are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:40.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們明早就動身\N{\rENG}We leave in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.96,0:09:24.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,夏綠蒂\N{\rENG}Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:26.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子在這裡\N{\rENG}The children are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:31.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.43,0:09:37.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,夏綠蒂阿姨！\N{\rENG}Aunt Charlotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.97,0:09:40.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,瑪格莉特，威廉，看看你們\N{\rENG}Margaret, William, look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.94,0:09:43.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,好想你\N{\rENG}Missed you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.19,0:09:47.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們長得好大，你給他們吃了什麼啊？\N{\rENG}They're huge. What have you been feeding them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.65,0:09:51.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的種好，因為是遺傳自母親\N{\rENG}Well, they're from good stock. On their mother's side, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.20,0:09:55.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝，進來吧，我有不少好東西\N{\rENG}Thank you. Come inside. Wait until you see what I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.99,0:09:58.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,給我們的禮物？　慢慢來\N{\rENG}- Presents? Presents for us? - Move slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.66,0:10:01.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們看好那些野蠻人，好嗎？\N{\rENG}Keep an eye on these heathens, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.62,0:10:04.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起\N{\rENG}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.80,0:10:16.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我幫你準備了這個，蘇珊，是你媽的\N{\rENG}I have this for you, Susan. It belonged to your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.02,0:10:25.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,她還是不開口？\N{\rENG}She's still not talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.56,0:10:27.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.82,0:10:32.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,看到你，我的感覺真好\N{\rENG}It does me good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.13,0:10:50.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,看，那是佳百列\N{\rENG}Look, there's Gabriel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.71,0:10:52.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列\N{\rENG}Gabriel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.22,0:10:59.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,吊死喬治國王！\N{\rENG}Hang King George!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.02,0:11:10.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈利·布林在招兵\N{\rENG}Harry Burwell is here recruiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.40,0:11:13.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,州長已經發誓，如果議會給大陸軍\N{\rENG}The governor has vowed if the assembly votes a single shilling...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.53,0:11:16.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,支持一分錢，就會解散議會\N{\rENG}...to the Continental Army, he'll dissolve the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.24,0:11:20.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是否使我們在賓州的代表…\N{\rENG}Wouldn't that force our delegates in Philadelphia 
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.76,0:11:22.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,一定要投獨立的票？\N{\rENG}to vote for independence?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.16,0:11:24.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.62,0:11:29.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,使我們在麻省附近發生戰爭\N{\rENG}Send us off to war alongside Massachusetts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:34.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,處死喬治國王！\N{\rENG}Get King George!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.96,0:11:38.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他們全都吊死！　一個都不要放過！\N{\rENG}- Hang them all! - Hang the lot of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.55,0:11:41.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,夠了，很好，孩子，進去吧\N{\rENG}That's enough. Very well, children, inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.81,0:11:45.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,走吧，進去\N{\rENG}Come along now. Inside now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.53,0:11:57.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,布林指靠你的選票\N{\rENG}Burwell will be counting on your vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.40,0:12:00.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,他希望成為第一個當選的人\N{\rENG}And he'll expect you to be the first to enlist.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:03.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，我想是\N{\rENG}Yes, I imagine so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.54,0:12:09.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起，這些野蠻人是…\N{\rENG}I'm sorry, the heathens are...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:13.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們非常渴望一個女人\N{\rENG}They have long needed a woman in their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.34,0:12:15.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個媽媽\N{\rENG}A mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.96,0:12:18.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,特別是蘇珊\N{\rENG}Especially Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:32.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是彼得·霍爾\N{\rENG}My name is Peter Howard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.73,0:12:36.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我喪失了大部份的聽力和我的左腿…\N{\rENG}I lost most of my hearing and my left leg...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.69,0:12:40.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,全都是為了法國和印第安人之間的戰事\N{\rENG}...fighting for the Crown in the French and Indian War.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.82,0:12:43.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,喬治國王是怎麼報答我的？\N{\rENG}And how did King George reward me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:46.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,他用稅廢了我另一條腿\N{\rENG}He cuts off my other leg with his taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.08,0:12:49.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,是你嗎，霍華小姐？\N{\rENG}Miss Howard, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.04,0:12:52.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道我是誰，佳百列·馬汀\N{\rENG}You know who I am, Gabriel Martin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.50,0:12:56.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們最後一次見面，我才11歲\N{\rENG}The last time you saw me, I was 11 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.80,0:12:58.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在我茶中加了墨水\N{\rENG}and you put ink in my tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:03.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,那應該是我弟弟吧，也許是山繆或納森\N{\rENG}I believe that was one of my younger brothers. Perhaps Samuel or Nathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.18,0:13:08.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,是你，那讓我的牙齒黑了一個月\N{\rENG}It was you, and it turned my teeth black for a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.85,0:13:16.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們就給喬治國王一個永生難忘的教訓吧\N{\rENG}- And send a message to King George he will never forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.94,0:13:19.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的第一個議題\N{\rENG}Our first order of business...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:21.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,也是最後的，讓我們來投票表決徵兵！\N{\rENG}And our last, if we vote a levy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.95,0:13:23.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,安靜…！\N{\rENG}Order, order!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.16,0:13:25.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,西門斯先生，你沒有發言權\N{\rENG}Mr. Simms, you do not have the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.62,0:13:29.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,首先是哈利·布林上校對獨立軍的演說\N{\rENG}First, an address by Colonel Harry Burwell of the Continental Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.91,0:13:31.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,布林上校\N{\rENG}Colonel Burwell.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.13,0:13:37.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,大家都知道我為什麼來這兒\N{\rENG}You all know why I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.75,0:13:39.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不是個演說家\N{\rENG}I'm not an orator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.26,0:13:45.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也不想說服大家接受我們作戰的理由\N{\rENG}And I would not try to convince you of the worthiness of our cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.80,0:13:47.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是個軍人\N{\rENG}I'm a soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:50.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們正在作戰\N{\rENG}And we are at war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.98,0:13:54.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們在等賓州發表獨立宣言\N{\rENG}From Philadelphia, we expect a declaration of independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.31,0:13:57.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,13個州中有8個州都決定出資…\N{\rENG}8 of the 13 colonies have levied money...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.98,0:14:00.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,贊助獨立軍\N{\rENG}...in support of a continental army.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.57,0:14:02.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望南卡能夠成為第9個州\N{\rENG}I ask that South Carolina be the ninth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.49,0:14:06.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,麻州和維吉尼亞州也許在打仗…\N{\rENG}Massachusetts and Virginia may be at war...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:09.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是南卡不是！\N{\rENG}...but South Carolina is not!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.29,0:14:10.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,贊成…\N{\rENG}Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:14.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,這一?鰬??皇菫闋幦∫粌?€州的獨立…\N{\rENG}This is not a war for the independence of one or two colonies...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:17.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,而是爭取整個國家的獨立\N{\rENG}...but for the independence of one nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.38,0:14:19.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,哪個國家呢？\N{\rENG}And what nation is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.71,0:14:21.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國！\N{\rENG}An American nation!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.13,0:14:24.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有這個國家，這麼說是叛國\N{\rENG}There is no such nation and to speak of one is treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.97,0:14:27.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們是美國的國民\N{\rENG}We are citizens of an American nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.10,0:14:30.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的權利卻受到三千英哩外…\N{\rENG}And our rights are being threatened...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.93,0:14:33.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,暴君的威脅\N{\rENG}...by a tyrant 3000 miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.77,0:14:36.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,霍華先生，請告訴我\N{\rENG}Would you tell me, please, Mr. Howard...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:40.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我為什麼要用三千哩外的暴君…\N{\rENG}...why should I trade one tyrant 3000 miles away...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.53,0:14:43.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,來換一英哩外的三千個暴君？\N{\rENG}...for 3000 tyrants one mile away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.37,0:14:50.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,民選國會也能像國王一樣\N{\rENG}An elected legislature can trample
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:52.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,踐踏我們的人權\N{\rENG}a man's rights as easily as a king can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:55.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬汀上尉…\N{\rENG}Captain Martin...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.75,0:14:58.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道你很愛國\N{\rENG}...I understood you to be a patriot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.00,0:15:02.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你想知道我是否因遭重稅而憤憤不平？\N{\rENG}If you mean by "patriot," am I angry about taxation without representation?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.76,0:15:04.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，我很生氣\N{\rENG}Well, yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.18,0:15:09.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,美國是否該獨立自主？\N{\rENG}Should the American colonies govern themselves independently?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.85,0:15:12.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我認為他們可以也應該\N{\rENG}I believe they can. And they should.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:17.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,但若你問我是否該跟英國宣戰…\N{\rENG}But if you're asking me am I willing to go to war with England...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.35,0:15:19.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的答覆是否定的\N{\rENG}...then the answer is most definitely no.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.44,0:15:28.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,難道這就是在英法戰爭時…\N{\rENG}This from the same Captain Benjamin Martin whose fury was so famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.12,0:15:30.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,怒氣勃發的馬汀上尉說的話嗎？\N{\rENG}...during the Wilderness campaign?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.41,0:15:34.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,當年我年少輕狂\N{\rENG}I was intemperate in my youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.45,0:15:36.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,節制很可能是恐懼的偽裝\N{\rENG}Temperance can be a disguise for fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:40.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,米德頓先生，我和馬汀上尉…\N{\rENG}Mr. Middleton, I fought with Captain Martin...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.21,0:15:42.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,一起在華盛頓將軍的麾下打過仗\N{\rENG}...under Washington in the French and Indian War.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.59,0:15:45.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,這屋裡沒有任何人…\N{\rENG}There's not a man in this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:49.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,比他還值得我信任的\N{\rENG}...or anywhere for that matter, to whom I would more willingly trust my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.60,0:15:52.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,除了戰爭還有別的選擇\N{\rENG}There are alternatives to war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.10,0:15:56.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們可以向國王陳情\N{\rENG}We take our case before the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.27,0:15:57.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們可以跟他講理　　我們試過了\N{\rENG}- We plead with him. - We tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.94,0:16:01.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我們應一試再試，極力避免戰爭\N{\rENG}Well, then, we try again and again if necessary to avoid a war.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:04.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我參加過邦克山之役\N{\rENG}I was at Bunker Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.32,0:16:07.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,英軍推進了三次\N{\rENG}The British advanced three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:09.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們近距離殺了七百名英軍\N{\rENG}We killed 700 at point-blank range 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.85,0:16:11.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,但他們仍然攻下邦克山\N{\rENG}and still they took the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:14.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是他們解決的方式\N{\rENG}That is the measure of their resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.95,0:16:18.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你的原則是堅持獨立…\N{\rENG}If your principles dictate independence...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.33,0:16:20.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,那唯有作戰一途\N{\rENG}...then war is the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:22.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰爭是無法避免的\N{\rENG}It is come to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.09,0:16:24.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,對…\N{\rENG}Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.67,0:16:28.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有七個小孩\N{\rENG}I have seven children.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:30.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,內人已死\N{\rENG}My wife is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.68,0:16:34.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我去作戰誰來照顧他們？\N{\rENG}Now, who's to care for them if I go to war?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.43,0:16:40.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,不光是沒有小孩的男人才去作戰\N{\rENG}Wars are not fought only by childless men.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.27,0:16:42.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,同意\N{\rENG}Granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:47.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,但請記下我的話\N{\rENG}But mark my words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:53.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,這場戰爭將不是在前線進行…\N{\rENG}This war will be fought, not on the frontier...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.78,0:16:56.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,也不是在遙遠的戰場…\N{\rENG}...or on some distant battlefield...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.66,0:16:59.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰火會在身邊燃燒\N{\rENG}...but amongst us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.50,0:17:01.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,在我們的家中燃燒\N{\rENG}Among our homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.63,0:17:06.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的孩子們將會親身體驗戰爭的可怕\N{\rENG}Our children will learn of it with their own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.67,0:17:11.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的童真將會和我們一起死去\N{\rENG}And the innocent will die with the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.51,0:17:17.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不參戰\N{\rENG}I will not fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.14,0:17:21.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,正因為如此，我不打算參與投票…\N{\rENG}And because I will not fight, I will not cast a vote...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.14,0:17:23.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,將別人送上戰場\N{\rENG}...that will send others to fight in my stead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.11,0:17:28.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的原則呢？\N{\rENG}And your principles?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.65,0:17:35.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是有孩子的人，我沒有講原則的權利\N{\rENG}I'm a parent. I haven't got the luxury of principles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.83,0:17:45.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們一定要投票贊成徵兵！\N{\rENG}We must vote to levy!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.18,0:18:02.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,28比l2！徵兵通過了！\N{\rENG}28 to 12! The levy passed!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:34.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,你打算擅自入伍？\N{\rENG}You intend to enlist without my permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.34,0:18:36.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.52,0:18:46.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親，我還以為你是個有原則的人\N{\rENG}Father, I thought you were a man of principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.44,0:18:53.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有家室後自會明白\N{\rENG}When you have a family of your own, perhaps you'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.41,0:19:00.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有家室，也不會用他們來當擋箭牌\N{\rENG}When I have a family of my own, I won't hide behind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:19.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,他像他父親小時候一樣魯莽\N{\rENG}He's as imprudent as his father was at his age.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.10,0:19:21.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,恐怕是這樣\N{\rENG}Regrettably so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:27.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會儘量將他收在我的羽翼之下\N{\rENG}I'll see to it that he serves under me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.27,0:19:31.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我叫他去做文官，或補給官之類的\N{\rENG}Make him a clerk or quartermaster, something of that sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:35.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,祝你好運\N{\rENG}Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.39,0:20:02.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,親愛的湯瑪斯，雖然過了許多年…\N{\rENG}Dear Thomas: Though many seasons have passed...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.06,0:20:07.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,但在查理士城見面，仿佛是昨日的事\N{\rENG}...it seems like only yesterday when we last saw each other in Charles Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.98,0:20:11.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,很遺憾聽說，英軍在康瓦理斯將軍指揮下…\N{\rENG}With sadness, I learned of its recent fall to the British...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.31,0:20:12.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,打敗我們的消息\N{\rENG}...under General Cornwallis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.11,0:20:19.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我今天接到夏綠蒂阿姨的信…\N{\rENG}I received a letter from Aunt Charlotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.20,0:20:22.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我…她在查理士城淪陷後鎖上家門…\N{\rENG}...saying she closed her home in Charles Town after the city fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.95,0:20:25.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,然後搬到山提河畔的農場\N{\rENG}...and moved to her plantation on the Santee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.17,0:20:40.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,在北邊我們彈盡糧絕\N{\rENG}Here in the north, our campaign has been marked by defeat and privation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.51,0:20:44.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們傷亡慘重\N{\rENG}Our losses have been grievous.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.94,0:20:55.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的好友彼德·庫本，在伊莉莎白鎮戰死\N{\rENG}My good friend, Peter Cuppin, fell at Elizabethtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.95,0:21:04.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的死訊讓我傷痛欲絕\N{\rENG}His death has been difficult to bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.59,0:21:20.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們即將和蓋茲將軍南進…\N{\rENG}We will march south with General Gates...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.26,0:21:23.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,和康瓦理斯將軍的紅衫軍對決\N{\rENG}...to fight the Redcoats under Cornwallis.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:27.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你，長官\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.07,0:21:42.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,我羡慕你…\N{\rENG}I envy you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.86,0:21:44.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我羡慕你和戰爭毫無瓜葛\N{\rENG}...your youth and distance from this cruel conflict of
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.93,0:21:48.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,而我卻是這場戰爭的一部份\N{\rENG} which I am a part.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.79,0:21:52.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我覺得，自己有幸能夠為自由而戰\N{\rENG}"But I am fortunate to be serving the cause of Liberty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.00,0:21:54.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,雖然我畏懼死亡…\N{\rENG}And though I fear death...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.13,0:21:58.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,但每天我都祈禱，我在必要時…\N{\rENG}...each day in prayer I reaffirm my willingness...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.13,0:22:00.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,能為自由捐軀\N{\rENG}...to give my life in its service.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.38,0:22:02.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,為我禱告\N{\rENG}Pray for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.09,0:22:06.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,為爭取自由而禱告\N{\rENG}But above all, pray for the cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.60,0:22:09.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,愛你的哥哥，佳百列上\N{\rENG}Your loving brother, Gabriel."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.76,0:22:46.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在做什麼？\N{\rENG}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.52,0:22:54.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,轉身\N{\rENG}Turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.77,0:23:01.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在還不行，湯瑪斯\N{\rENG}Not yet, Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.28,0:23:03.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,那什麼時候？\N{\rENG}When?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.45,0:23:09.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,等你17歲\N{\rENG}Seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.08,0:23:13.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,那還要兩年，我已經等了兩年\N{\rENG}That's two years. It's already been two.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.08,0:23:18.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,到時戰爭說不定結束了　　老天保佑\N{\rENG}- The war could be over by then. - God willing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.38,0:23:24.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,17歲就17歲\N{\rENG}All right. Seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:28.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.23,0:23:37.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,請放回去\N{\rENG}Put it back, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.90,0:23:43.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親？\N{\rENG}Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.61,0:23:46.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,威爾德尼斯堡發生了什麼事？\N{\rENG}What happened at Fort Wilderness?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.20,0:23:51.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,收好\N{\rENG}Put it away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.50,0:24:00.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,扔遠一點　　你扔遠一點，你來\N{\rENG}- Throw it faster. - You throw it faster. You're the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.97,0:24:16.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,瑪格莉特，你讓弟弟馬上回來這裡\N{\rENG}Margaret, you go get your brothers back up here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.58,0:25:25.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,回屋去，快\N{\rENG}Back to the house. Come on. Back to the house now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.38,0:25:29.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟我來，瑪格莉特，快\N{\rENG}Come with me. Margaret, go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.64,0:25:37.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們快來了\N{\rENG}They're going to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:40.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,靜點，坐下\N{\rENG}Quiet. Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.63,0:26:14.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,六磅炮\N{\rENG}Six-pounders.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:15.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,好多\N{\rENG}Lots of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.60,0:26:17.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,有多遠？\N{\rENG}How far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.89,0:26:22.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,還遠著呢，看來是瞄準別的方向\N{\rENG}They're a long way off. They're most likely heading the other direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.65,0:26:26.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,把槍收進去\N{\rENG}Put those in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.73,0:26:30.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們可能朝這裡來　　要我再說一遍嗎？\N{\rENG}- They might come this way. - Must I tell you again?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.70,0:26:35.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們全躲在家裡，懂嗎？\N{\rENG}Let's all stay close in to the house, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.76,0:26:57.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要趕走英軍\N{\rENG}We'll have to fight them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.51,0:26:59.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親不會這麼做嗎？\N{\rENG}Won't Father do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.27,0:27:02.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們也許會殺了我們男人…\N{\rENG}They'll probably kill us men...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.52,0:27:06.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,淩虐你們女生\N{\rENG}...and do Lord-knows-what to you women.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.90,0:27:08.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,納森！\N{\rENG}Nathan!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.05,0:27:36.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,慢慢轉過來\N{\rENG}Slowly turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.14,0:27:41.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親\N{\rENG}Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.43,0:27:45.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾比佳！\N{\rENG}Abigale!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.52,0:27:48.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,快去拿水和繃帶\N{\rENG}Water and bandages, fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.98,0:27:54.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有在作戰現場嗎？\N{\rENG}The battle. Were you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.36,0:27:56.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有看見紅衫軍嗎？\N{\rENG}Have you seen any Redcoats?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.20,0:27:58.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,還沒有\N{\rENG}No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.03,0:28:01.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾比佳，快去照顧孩子們\N{\rENG}Abigale, the children, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.79,0:28:04.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子們，跟我上樓\N{\rENG}Children, come. Upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.96,0:28:12.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,蓋茲帶著我們直搗紅衫軍黃龍\N{\rENG}Gates marched us straight at the Redcoats.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.55,0:28:16.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的防線失散了，被英軍打得潰不成軍\N{\rENG}Our lines broke. The British Green Dragoons cut us to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.55,0:28:18.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,上級給我?@些急件\N{\rENG}I was given these dispatches.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.18,0:28:23.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我離開時，看到維吉尼亞正規軍投降\N{\rENG}As I left, I saw the Virginia Regulars surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.14,0:28:28.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,英軍長驅直入\N{\rENG}The Dragoons rode into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.81,0:28:30.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他們殺光了\N{\rENG}Killed them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.19,0:28:33.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩百多個人\N{\rENG}Over 200 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.32,0:28:37.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一定要把這些急件送到西爾斯堡\N{\rENG}I have to get these dispatches to Hillsborough.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.11,0:28:38.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不能騎馬\N{\rENG}You can't ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.53,0:28:41.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不能留在這，我在這裡會危及…\N{\rENG}I can't stay here! It's not safe for...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.11,0:29:15.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.91,0:29:25.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.14,0:31:51.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你們照顧國王的士兵\N{\rENG}Thank you for the care of His Majesty's soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.84,0:32:25.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,中尉，派一隊人馬送傷兵去看醫生\N{\rENG}Have a detachment take our wounded to our surgeons at Winnsboro.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.38,0:32:27.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，長官\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.34,0:32:30.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,放火燒了那棟房子和穀倉\N{\rENG}Fire the house and barns.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.97,0:32:36.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們要是敢窩藏敵軍，就會無家可歸\N{\rENG}Let it be known if you harbour the enemy you will lose your home.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.23,0:32:42.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,喬治國王有令…\N{\rENG}By order of King George...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.32,0:32:45.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,任何只要為英國效力的美國奴隸\N{\rENG}...all slaves of the American colonies who fight for the Crown...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.03,0:32:49.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,只要我們戰勝就能成為自由之身\N{\rENG}...will be granted their freedom with our victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.37,0:32:54.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不是奴隸，是在這工作的自由人\N{\rENG}We're not slaves. We work this land. We're freedmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.16,0:32:58.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,那各位就是有幸為…\N{\rENG}Then you're freedmen who will have the privilege...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.50,0:33:00.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,英國軍隊效力的自由人了\N{\rENG}...of fighting in the king's army.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.59,0:33:08.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,敵軍的快遞，長官\N{\rENG}Rebel dispatches, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.85,0:33:16.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是誰的？\N{\rENG}Who carried this?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.40,0:33:26.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰的？！\N{\rENG}Who carried this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.49,0:33:28.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的\N{\rENG}I did, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.45,0:33:37.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我受傷了，這些人照顧我\N{\rENG}I was wounded. These people gave me care.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.46,0:33:40.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們和這些密令沒有關係\N{\rENG}They have nothing to do with the dispatches.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.79,0:33:45.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,帶他去坎登，他是間諜\N{\rENG}Take this one to Camden. He is a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.92,0:33:48.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,吊死他，屍首示眾\N{\rENG}Hang him, put his body on display.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.59,0:33:50.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是個傳令兵\N{\rENG}He's a dispatch rider.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.68,0:33:53.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,殺了活口把馬留給英軍\N{\rENG}Destroy the livestock. Save the horses for the Dragoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.10,0:33:57.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,上校，他是帶著密令的制服傳令兵\N{\rENG}Colonel, this is a uniformed dispatch rider carrying a marked case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.14,0:33:59.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不能被視為間諜\N{\rENG}He cannot be held as a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.68,0:34:02.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不打算關他，我們要吊死他\N{\rENG}Well, we won't hold him. We're going to hang him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.98,0:34:07.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,上校…　父親！\N{\rENG}- Colonel... - Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.95,0:34:13.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我懂了，他是你兒子\N{\rENG}Oh, I see. He's your son.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.91,0:34:17.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許你該教他什麼叫做愛國\N{\rENG}Perhaps you should've taught him something of loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.12,0:34:23.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,上校，我求你根據作戰時的規定…\N{\rENG}Colonel, I beg you, please reconsider. By the rules of war...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.54,0:34:27.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想知道什麼叫作戰規則嗎？\N{\rENG}Would you like a lesson, sir, in the rules of war?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.05,0:34:31.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許你的小孩想上一課\N{\rENG}Or perhaps your children would.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.89,0:34:38.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,無此必要\N{\rENG}No lesson is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.52,0:34:42.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,長官\N{\rENG}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.85,0:34:44.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,那些受傷的叛軍怎麼辦？\N{\rENG}What of the rebel wounded?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.15,0:34:48.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,殺了他們\N{\rENG}Kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.36,0:34:54.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親\N{\rENG}Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.58,0:35:00.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親，快想想辦法！\N{\rENG}Father, do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.58,0:35:01.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,安靜！\N{\rENG}Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.38,0:35:16.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列，快跑！\N{\rENG}Gabriel, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.39,0:35:18.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等！\N{\rENG}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.14,0:35:22.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,不！！\N{\rENG}No!!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.96,0:35:50.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,愚蠢的孩子\N{\rENG}Stupid boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.84,0:35:58.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,上尉\N{\rENG}Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.85,0:36:04.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯瑪斯！\N{\rENG}Thomas!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.03,0:37:01.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,來吧，孩子\N{\rENG}Come, child.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.24,0:37:05.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,不　　我不會留下這些孩子！\N{\rENG}I'm not leaving these children!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.91,0:37:07.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,手下留情！\N{\rENG}Mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.54,0:37:10.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備！\N{\rENG}Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.25,0:37:11.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,舉槍！\N{\rENG}Present!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.46,0:37:12.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.76,0:37:58.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們都留在這裡\N{\rENG}All of you, stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.58,0:38:35.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,納森，山繆\N{\rENG}Nathan, Samuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.84,0:38:41.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,瑪格莉特\N{\rENG}Margaret.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.43,0:38:45.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要你們帶著威廉和蘇珊躲在田裡\N{\rENG}Hide in the fields with William and Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.18,0:38:49.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,若我黃昏時沒回來，就去找夏綠蒂阿姨\N{\rENG}If we're not back by sunset, take them to Aunt Charlotte's.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.18,0:38:51.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,懂了嗎？\N{\rENG}- Is that clear? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.23,0:38:53.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子們\N{\rENG}Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.70,0:39:47.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個地點不錯\N{\rENG}It's a good spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.37,0:39:51.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子們，聽我說\N{\rENG}Boys, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.00,0:39:53.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我先開槍\N{\rENG}I'll fire first.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.79,0:39:58.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要你們先開槍打軍官，再打士兵\N{\rENG}Start with the officers and work your way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.92,0:40:00.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們知道哪些是軍官吧？\N{\rENG}Can you tell the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.80,0:40:01.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道，父親\N{\rENG}Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.09,0:40:03.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,知道　　很好\N{\rENG}- Yes, Father. - Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.47,0:40:08.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,山繆，在你開第一槍後就幫納森裝子彈\N{\rENG}Samuel, after your first shot, reload for Nathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.14,0:40:09.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在…\N{\rENG}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.43,0:40:12.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,萬一我有個三長兩短，我要你們放下武器\N{\rENG}...if anything should happen to me, drop your weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.39,0:40:14.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,能跑多快就跑多快\N{\rENG}Run as quickly as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.14,0:40:16.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,回家去找弟弟，妹妹…\N{\rENG}Get your brother and your sisters...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.94,0:40:19.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,帶他們去夏綠蒂阿姨家，懂嗎？\N{\rENG}...and take them to Aunt Charlotte's. Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.23,0:40:22.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,還記得我教你們怎麼開槍嗎？\N{\rENG}What did I say about shooting?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.40,0:40:24.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄小目標失誤就少\N{\rENG}Aim small, miss small.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.15,0:40:26.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄小目標失誤就少\N{\rENG}Aim small, miss small.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.07,0:40:29.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,孩子們…\N{\rENG}Boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.74,0:40:31.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,山繆…\N{\rENG}...Samuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.45,0:40:32.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要慌\N{\rENG}...steady.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.33,0:41:22.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,上帝，保佑我又快又准\N{\rENG}Lord, make me fast and accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.34,0:41:26.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄小目標失誤就少\N{\rENG}Aim small, miss small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.97,0:41:29.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄小目標失誤就少\N{\rENG}Aim small, miss small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.97,0:41:32.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄小目標失誤就少\N{\rENG}Aim small, miss small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.44,0:41:47.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,上面，在右邊！　在左邊！\N{\rENG}- On the right! - To the left!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.24,0:41:56.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,在後面！\N{\rENG}Behind us! Up on the ridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.83,0:42:02.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,從右邊來的！\N{\rENG}Form right!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.17,0:42:05.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,右轉！\N{\rENG}To the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.30,0:42:08.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,向後轉！\N{\rENG}About face!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.51,0:42:13.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,在右邊的山上！\N{\rENG}On the right to the rear!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.35,0:42:15.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,向右轉！\N{\rENG}To the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.01,0:42:17.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.22,0:42:20.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,裝子彈！　裝子彈！\N{\rENG}- Reload! - Reload!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.62,0:42:41.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,在後面！\N{\rENG}Behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.92,0:42:47.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,注意後面！\N{\rENG}Look on the rear!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.31,0:47:16.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,上帝\N{\rENG}Lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.69,0:47:20.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們祈禱您接受這個孩子\N{\rENG}...we pray that you accept this child...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.57,0:47:23.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓他和他媽留在您身邊\N{\rENG}...and keep him at your side with his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.74,0:47:27.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們請求你收留他\N{\rENG}We ask that you embrace him...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.79,0:47:34.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,幫助我們理解你的仁慈\N{\rENG}...and help us to understand the manner in which your mercy works.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.67,0:47:37.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,原諒我們的罪行\N{\rENG}And forgive us our sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.67,0:47:40.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們以您的名義祈禱\N{\rENG}This we ask in your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.01,0:47:42.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,阿門\N{\rENG}Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.78,0:48:11.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們印地安斥候帶回來的二等兵\N{\rENG}Sir, we have the private the Cherokee scouts brought in.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.13,0:48:23.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,二等兵？\N{\rENG}Private?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.84,0:48:24.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,二等兵\N{\rENG}Private.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.09,0:48:27.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是青龍部隊的威廉·塔維頓上校\N{\rENG}Colonel William Tavington, Green Dragoons.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.97,0:48:30.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼了？誰幹的好事？\N{\rENG}What happened? Who did this?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.18,0:48:32.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,他\N{\rENG}Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.60,0:48:35.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,當?r情況一團亂\N{\rENG}It was mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.89,0:48:37.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也說不上來是誰幹的\N{\rENG}I couldn't tell you who it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.77,0:48:39.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,冷靜點…\N{\rENG}Calm down. Calm down, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.48,0:48:43.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們損失了20名皇家士兵\N{\rENG}Twenty of His Majesty's soldiers are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.53,0:48:45.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要知道是怎麼回事\N{\rENG}And I need to know how.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.11,0:48:48.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說有…　你在場嗎？\N{\rENG}- He said there was... - Were you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.78,0:48:50.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就讓他說\N{\rENG}Then let him speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.33,0:48:54.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,慢慢來，告訴我有多少人？\N{\rENG}Take your time and tell me. How many were there?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.08,0:48:56.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,是民兵嗎？還是正規軍？\N{\rENG}Were they militia? Were they Regulars?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.50,0:48:59.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不記得有多少人\N{\rENG}I don't really remember how many.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.25,0:49:03.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許只有一個\N{\rENG}Maybe one.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.59,0:49:08.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,一個人，真的嗎？\N{\rENG}One man. Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.39,0:49:10.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在側面攻擊\N{\rENG}He was in the flank.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.60,0:49:13.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,似乎在我們周邊遊走\N{\rENG}All around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.60,0:49:15.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,又仿佛在我們之間\N{\rENG}Amongst us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.68,0:49:18.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,他來無影去無蹤，我幾乎看不到他\N{\rENG}I could barely see him. He was there, then he was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.44,0:49:20.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,他就這樣消失了\N{\rENG}He just vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.31,0:49:23.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽起來像鬼不像人\N{\rENG}Sounds more like a ghost than a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.07,0:49:25.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,鬼\N{\rENG}A ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.07,0:49:28.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是很像鬼\N{\rENG}He was like a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.37,0:49:31.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,夠了\N{\rENG}Enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.83,0:49:36.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,波頓？帶一隊偵察隊\N{\rENG}Bordon? Take a patrol.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.75,0:49:39.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,看看能不能在消息傳開前抓到這個鬼\N{\rENG}Capture this ghost before word of his exploits spread.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.92,0:49:42.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是誰？　他是威爾金上尉\N{\rENG}- Who's this? - Sir, this is Captain Wilkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.04,0:49:46.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,他曾是英國民兵，說不定派得上用場\N{\rENG}He was with the Loyalist Colonial Militia. He might be of use.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.05,0:49:48.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,又一個殖民地居民\N{\rENG}Another colonial.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.34,0:49:51.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,威爾金上尉，你忠於哪一方？\N{\rENG}Captain Wilkins, where do your loyalties lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.10,0:49:53.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我忠於英王和祖國\N{\rENG}To king and country.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.51,0:49:56.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我為什麼要信任一個出賣鄰居的人？\N{\rENG}Why should I trust a man who'd betray his neighbours?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.81,0:49:59.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我那些出賣英國的鄰居…\N{\rENG}Those neighbours of mine who stand against England...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.06,0:50:01.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,罪該萬死\N{\rENG}...deserve to die a traitor's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.94,0:50:03.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,咱們走著瞧吧\N{\rENG}We'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.28,0:50:11.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬汀先生！\N{\rENG}Mr. Martin!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.08,0:50:19.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,夏綠蒂小姐…！\N{\rENG}Miss Charlotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.34,0:50:34.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們安全了，睡吧\N{\rENG}You're safe now. Try to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.35,0:50:35.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安\N{\rENG}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.97,0:50:37.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,晚安\N{\rENG}Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.68,0:50:39.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親？\N{\rENG}Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.27,0:50:40.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼事？\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.48,0:50:43.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,我殺了那些人\N{\rENG}I killed those men.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.86,0:50:46.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你只是照我的話去做\N{\rENG}You did what I told you to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.78,0:50:50.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是你該做的，這沒什麼不對\N{\rENG}You did what you had to. There was no wrong in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.32,0:50:55.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很高興殺了他們\N{\rENG}I'm glad I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.08,0:51:00.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,我真的很高興\N{\rENG}I'm glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.47,0:51:11.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,睡吧\N{\rENG}Get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.64,0:51:20.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,山繆\N{\rENG}Samuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.71,0:51:45.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,你做了…沒什麼好覺得羞恥的事\N{\rENG}You've done nothing for which you should be ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.92,0:51:48.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我什麼都沒做\N{\rENG}I've done nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.30,0:51:52.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以我很羞愧\N{\rENG}And for that, I am ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.38,0:52:34.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要去聖海倫納\N{\rENG}We'll go to Saint Helena.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.47,0:52:38.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,在查理士城南邊，是個自由奴隸島\N{\rENG}That's a free slave island just north of Charles Town.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.68,0:52:41.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在英國人的眼皮底下\N{\rENG}Right under the British noses.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.43,0:52:44.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們不會想…　我要去加入他們\N{\rENG}- They won't think of look... - I'm joining up with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.44,0:52:46.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列\N{\rENG}Gabriel.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.06,0:52:51.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,不，你得留在這裡\N{\rENG}No. Your place is here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.15,0:52:54.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要回去，我是個軍人，這是我的職責\N{\rENG}I'm going back. I'm a soldier, it's my duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.28,0:52:56.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要對你的家庭負責\N{\rENG}Your duty is to your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.11,0:52:59.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,不准你棄我於不顧！\N{\rENG}Don't you walk away from me, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.16,0:53:01.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰爭結束後我會來找你們\N{\rENG}I'll find you when it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.58,0:53:03.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不准你去！\N{\rENG}No, I forbid you to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.66,0:53:07.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不是個小孩！　你是我的小孩！\N{\rENG}- I'm not a child! - You're my child!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.88,0:53:10.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見，父親\N{\rENG}Goodbye, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.50,0:53:13.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列\N{\rENG}Gabriel.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.96,0:53:15.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯瑪斯死了\N{\rENG}Thomas is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.17,0:53:19.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,到底要死多少人，你才肯聽我的話？\N{\rENG}How many more have to die before you'll heed my word?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.08,0:53:51.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在失去我的家人\N{\rENG}I'm losing my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.75,0:53:56.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親，你什麼時候會回來？\N{\rENG}When will you be back, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.88,0:53:59.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rENG}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.72,0:54:01.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,明天嗎？\N{\rENG}Tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.43,0:54:03.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是明天\N{\rENG}No, not tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.72,0:54:05.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,乖乖禱告\N{\rENG}You say your prayers.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.68,0:54:06.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會的\N{\rENG}I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.60,0:54:11.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,照顧弟弟、妹妹和夏綠蒂阿姨\N{\rENG}Take care of your brothers and sisters and your Aunt Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.44,0:54:13.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只能靠你了\N{\rENG}I'm depending on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.32,0:54:16.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有你，山繆\N{\rENG}As I am on you, Samuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.69,0:54:18.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,好\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.70,0:54:26.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,蘇珊\N{\rENG}Susan...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.16,0:54:30.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見\N{\rENG}...goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.39,0:54:46.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝！\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.73,0:56:56.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,停！\N{\rENG}Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.36,0:57:01.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備！\N{\rENG}Make ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.86,0:57:08.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄準！\N{\rENG}Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.87,0:57:14.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.30,0:57:28.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會回去的\N{\rENG}I'm not going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.72,0:57:30.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我也沒有指望你回去\N{\rENG}No, I didn't expect you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.52,0:57:37.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個蓋茲是個傻瓜\N{\rENG}That Gates is a damn fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.77,0:57:42.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在英國部隊混了太久\N{\rENG}He spent too many years in the British army.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.40,0:57:46.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,居然想在曠野中擊敗紅衫軍，真瘋狂\N{\rENG}Going muzzle-to-muzzle with Redcoats in open field. It's madness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.15,0:57:48.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,停！\N{\rENG}Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.70,0:57:50.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備！\N{\rENG}Make ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.07,0:57:52.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,舉槍！\N{\rENG}Present!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.91,0:57:55.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.93,0:58:20.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,這場戰爭在開始前就結束了\N{\rENG}This battle was over before it began.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.24,0:58:31.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退！\N{\rENG}Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.12,0:58:33.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退！\N{\rENG}Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.04,0:58:43.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些鄉巴佬真笨\N{\rENG}These rustics are so inept.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.00,0:58:46.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,差點害我們贏得毫無光彩\N{\rENG}Nearly takes the honour out of victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.38,0:58:48.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,差一點\N{\rENG}Nearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.28,0:59:12.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\rENG}Hello general, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.53,0:59:15.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,今天是陛下和英格蘭的榮耀之日\N{\rENG}A glorious day for His Majesty and England.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.45,0:59:17.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓上校\N{\rENG}Colonel Tavington.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.83,0:59:20.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,總是太早\N{\rENG}Always too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.96,0:59:22.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,總是太渴求榮耀\N{\rENG}Always too eager for glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.79,0:59:26.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,渴求勝利\N{\rENG}For victory, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.13,0:59:29.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我相信我們已經佔領了地方\N{\rENG}I believe we took the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.17,0:59:31.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,下次，你要等我的命令\N{\rENG}Next time, you'll wait for my command.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.38,0:59:36.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓上校好像更喜歡聽自己下的命令\N{\rENG}It appears that Colonel Tavington prefers to follow his own commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.01,0:59:38.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,奧哈拉將軍告訴我…\N{\rENG}General O'Hara tells me...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.52,0:59:42.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,你得了一個“屠夫”的稱號\N{\rENG}...you've earned the nickname "The Butcher" among the populous.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.56,0:59:44.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們明天討論\N{\rENG}We'll discuss it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.90,0:59:47.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,諸位，我的讚揚\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, my compliments.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.69,0:59:50.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,慶祝勝利　　說得好！\N{\rENG}- To a victory. - Hear, hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.41,1:00:01.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,壓住他\N{\rENG}Hold him firm.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.72,1:00:23.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們的指揮官呢？　在那個帳篷裡\N{\rENG}- Where's your commanding officer? - That tent there.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.40,1:00:31.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是個失敗的行動\N{\rENG}It's a lost cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.00,1:00:49.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,班傑明·馬汀\N{\rENG}Benjamin Martin.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.75,1:00:51.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不想聽訓\N{\rENG}I'm in no mood for a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.09,1:00:54.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們的蓋茲將軍呢？\N{\rENG}Where's your General Gates now?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.76,1:00:58.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,有人看到他騎著馬朝東南方走了\N{\rENG}The last anyone saw, riding hard northeast...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.14,1:01:02.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的屬下在百碼後…苦苦追趕\N{\rENG}...his staff 100 yards behind, trying to catch up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.93,1:01:04.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在由誰指揮？\N{\rENG}So who's in command?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.23,1:01:06.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rENG}I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.48,1:01:08.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想\N{\rENG}I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.11,1:01:11.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要下什麼命令給我？\N{\rENG}What are my orders?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.40,1:01:19.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,班傑明，我們差一口氣就輸了\N{\rENG}We're a breath away from losing this war, Benjamin.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.41,1:01:25.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,華盛頓在莫瑞斯鎮重整軍備\N{\rENG}In the north, Washington is reeling from Morristown.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.66,1:01:28.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在躲一萬兩千名紅衫軍\N{\rENG}He's running and hiding from 12,000 Redcoats.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.58,1:01:31.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們在南方的軍隊又被康瓦理斯打散了\N{\rENG}In the south, Cornwallis has broken our back.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.34,1:01:34.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,他攻陷查理士城時，俘擄了我們五千弟兄\N{\rENG}Captured over 5000 of our troops when he took Charles Town.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.84,1:01:38.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,他也擊潰了唯一擋在他和紐約間的軍隊\N{\rENG}And he destroyed the only army between him and New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.68,1:01:43.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們無力阻擋他長驅直入擊敗華盛頓軍隊\N{\rENG}Nothing will stop him from heading north to finish off Washington.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.35,1:01:45.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,除非想辦法把康瓦理斯留在南方\N{\rENG}Unless we can keep Cornwallis in the south 
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.35,1:01:47.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,直到法軍抵達\N{\rENG}till the French arrive.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.35,1:01:51.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們答應要派一支艦隊和一萬名士兵來\N{\rENG}They've promised a fleet and 10,000 troops.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.48,1:01:53.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,何時？\N{\rENG}When?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.15,1:01:56.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,最快還要六個月\N{\rENG}Six months at the earliest.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.82,1:01:59.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,你相信法國人會言而有信？\N{\rENG}You trust the French to keep their word?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.36,1:02:00.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,那當然\N{\rENG}Absolument.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.03,1:02:05.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,班傑明·馬汀，這位是維倫少校\N{\rENG}Benjamin Martin. Major Jean Villeneuve.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.87,1:02:09.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是法國第七步兵連的，來幫我們訓練民兵\N{\rENG}French Seventh Light Foot. He will help train the militia.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.54,1:02:12.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是維爾德尼斯的英雄，久仰了\N{\rENG}The hero of Fort Wilderness. Your reputation precedes you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.72,1:02:20.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你真的想用民兵來阻止康瓦理斯推進？\N{\rENG}You really expect to hold Cornwallis here using just militia?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.09,1:02:23.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,不是我，是你\N{\rENG}Not me. You.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.64,1:02:27.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈利，他們不是軍人，是農民\N{\rENG}They're not soldiers, they're farmers.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.73,1:02:30.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓英軍通過…對他們比較好\N{\rENG}They'd be better off letting the British march through.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.60,1:02:33.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯，但形勢不允許\N{\rENG}They'd be better off, but the cause wouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.36,1:02:36.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,康瓦理斯手下有多少人？\N{\rENG}How many men does Cornwallis have?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.78,1:02:38.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,八千名步兵\N{\rENG}8000 infantry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.07,1:02:41.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,六百名騎兵\N{\rENG}Around 600 cavalry.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.70,1:02:44.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我任命你為上校\N{\rENG}I'm giving you a field commission as a colonel.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.70,1:02:47.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,長官，可以把我兒子派到我的部隊嗎？\N{\rENG}Might I request that you transfer my son under my command?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.58,1:02:49.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,長官，不，我…\N{\rENG}Sir, no, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.29,1:02:50.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,就這麼定了\N{\rENG}That's done.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.13,1:02:55.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.21,1:02:59.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,上校，我已經當了兩年兵\N{\rENG}Colonel, I've been a soldier for two years.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:59.42,1:03:01.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我當過斥候騎兵，狙擊兵，清道兵\N{\rENG}As a scout, horseman, marksman, scavenger.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.09,1:03:04.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,是嗎？　我在正規軍比較有發展\N{\rENG}- Is that so? - I'd be of better use with Regulars.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.85,1:03:06.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是從哪兒學會騎馬，開槍的？\N{\rENG}Where'd you learn all that riding, shooting, scavenging?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.18,1:03:08.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我父親教的\N{\rENG}My father taught me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.85,1:03:12.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,他有沒有教你如何謙虛？\N{\rENG}Teach you any humility?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.10,1:03:14.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,他試過，但我不受教\N{\rENG}He tried. It didn't take.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.19,1:03:19.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,他也教你認從這到查理士城的每條小路…\N{\rENG}He also taught you every trail between here and Charles Town...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.90,1:03:21.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以才會把你調過來\N{\rENG}...which is why he transferred you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.45,1:03:25.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們放話出去，我們從山提河南岸開始…\N{\rENG}We'll put the word out. Start on the south side of...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.33,1:03:27.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,分頭進行比較快\N{\rENG}We'll cover more ground if we split up.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.12,1:03:32.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好，下士\N{\rENG}Very well, corporal. 
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.52,1:03:34.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,你去哈利斯維爾、潘布克、維克菲爾德\N{\rENG}You take Harrisville, Pembroke, Wakefield.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.88,1:03:39.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,我從北邊開始，到黑沼澤會合\N{\rENG}I'll start on the north side. Meet at the mission in Black Swamp.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.05,1:03:44.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,下士\N{\rENG}Corporal.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.89,1:03:47.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,小心點\N{\rENG}Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.68,1:03:50.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,遵命\N{\rENG}Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.81,1:03:57.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有孩子嗎？\N{\rENG}You have children?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.03,1:04:03.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,法國人\N{\rENG}French.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.51,1:04:29.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,這從山上…\N{\rENG}It skirts the mountain and then...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.56,1:04:31.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,一直到這裡的水邊…\N{\rENG}...extends down towards the headwater here...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.14,1:04:35.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,跨越俄亥俄河\N{\rENG}...and right across to the far bank of the Ohio River.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.02,1:04:37.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,一共十萬英畝\N{\rENG}It's 100,000 acres.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.56,1:04:39.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,好大一片土地啊\N{\rENG}It's an imposing land grant, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.91,1:04:42.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以自己成立一個小國家\N{\rENG}You will be a country unto yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.29,1:04:48.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,國王真的很大方\N{\rENG}His Majesty is most generous.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.79,1:04:55.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是您在戰爭中的表現也當之無愧\N{\rENG}Though your service in this war more than warrants such a gift.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.59,1:05:00.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，國王對為他效命的人…\N{\rENG}Yes, this is how His Majesty rewards those...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.55,1:05:02.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是這麼大方\N{\rENG}...who fight for him as gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.89,1:05:06.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想我也有一天能得到獎賞吧\N{\rENG}I dare to presume my own meagre contributions will be rewarded one day.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.14,1:05:09.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想得太多了\N{\rENG}You may presume too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.90,1:05:13.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,國王看的不光是戰爭的結果…\N{\rENG}His Majesty, like history, judges us by the outcome of the war...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.69,1:05:15.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,也很注重作戰的過程\N{\rENG}...and the manner in which it was fought.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.82,1:05:20.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們為英國皇室打仗，就要有個作戰的樣子\N{\rENG}We serve the Crown, and we must conduct ourselves accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.70,1:05:22.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要善待投降的士兵\N{\rENG}Surrendering troops will be given quarter.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.12,1:05:25.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,這種慘無人道的事必須停止！\N{\rENG}These brutal tactics must stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.91,1:05:28.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,我百戰百勝還不夠嗎？\N{\rENG}Is it not enough that I have never lost a battle?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.58,1:05:29.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,你為我作戰…\N{\rENG}You serve me...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.96,1:05:34.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,你作戰的方式會影響別人對我的看法！\N{\rENG}...and the manner in which you serve me reflects upon me!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.30,1:05:38.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我以為像你這樣的名門子弟…\N{\rENG}I would've thought that a gentleman from a family as esteemed as yours...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.13,1:05:40.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,應該瞭解這點才是\N{\rENG}...would understand that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.51,1:05:45.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,我父親把我的遺產\N{\rENG}My late father squandered any esteem in which we were held...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.64,1:05:47.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,和自尊揮霍一空\N{\rENG}...along with my inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.94,1:05:53.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,打勝仗是我力爭上游的方式\N{\rENG}I advance myself only through victory.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.81,1:05:57.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要靠我的戰功才能得利\N{\rENG}You advance yourself only through my good graces.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.86,1:06:00.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,殖民地的人民是我們的弟兄\N{\rENG}These Colonials are our brethren.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.15,1:06:05.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰爭結束之後我們會重修舊好\N{\rENG}And when this conflict is over, we will re-establish commerce with them.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.45,1:06:08.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,懂嗎，上校？\N{\rENG}Do you understand, colonel?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.66,1:06:11.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,懂，大人\N{\rENG}Perfectly, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.29,1:06:57.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,牧師，如你允許，我想宣佈一件事\N{\rENG}Reverend, with your permission, I'd like to make an announcement.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.67,1:07:00.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,年輕人，這是上帝的聖地\N{\rENG}Young man, this is a house of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.34,1:07:03.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我瞭解，牧師，請容我道歉\N{\rENG}I understand that, reverend. I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.72,1:07:08.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們來召集南卡民兵\N{\rENG}The South Carolina Militia is being called up.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.14,1:07:11.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,有志加入的人請來我這兒登記\N{\rENG}I'm here to enlist every man willing.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.48,1:07:13.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,年輕人…\N{\rENG}Son...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.02,1:07:15.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們在這裡\N{\rENG}...we are here to pray...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.06,1:07:18.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,為在外面被吊死的人禱告\N{\rENG}...for the souls of those men hanging outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.11,1:07:20.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,為他們禱告吧\N{\rENG}Yes, pray for them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.23,1:07:23.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,但加入我們不要讓他們白死\N{\rENG}But honour them by taking up arms with us.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.36,1:07:27.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓人民吃更多苦？\N{\rENG}And bring more suffering to this town?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.78,1:07:31.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果英王喬治能吊死那些人 他就能吊死我們\N{\rENG}If King George can hang those men, he can hang any one of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.50,1:07:34.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,丹史考特…\N{\rENG}Dan Scott...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.87,1:07:38.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,一周前，你大贊獨立自主兩小時\N{\rENG}...barely a week ago you railed for two hours about independence.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.17,1:07:43.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈偉先生，你在我家提及過\N{\rENG}Mr. Hardwick, how many times have I heard you...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.97,1:07:46.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,多少次自由？\N{\rENG}...speak of freedom at my father's table?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.05,1:07:51.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡半數的人包括你父親…\N{\rENG}Half the men in this church, including you, Father...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.64,1:07:54.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,和你，牧師…\N{\rENG}...and you, reverend...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.89,1:07:57.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,都和我一樣愛國\N{\rENG}...are as ardent patriots as I.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.53,1:08:06.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們現在卻只敢空談嗎？\N{\rENG}Will you now, when you are needed most, stop at only words?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.49,1:08:09.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們是這種人嗎？\N{\rENG}Is that the sort of men you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.92,1:08:21.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要求你們起而行…\N{\rENG}I ask only that you act upon the beliefs...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.42,1:08:24.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,貫徹你們的理念…\N{\rENG}...of which you have so strongly spoken...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.17,1:08:28.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,為你們的信仰奮鬥\N{\rENG}...and in which you so strongly believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.48,1:08:41.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,誰要加入我們？\N{\rENG}Who's with us?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.75,1:09:44.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,霍華先生\N{\rENG}Mr. Howard.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.96,1:09:46.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生…\N{\rENG}Sir...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.46,1:09:49.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以寫信給安嗎？\N{\rENG}...may I have permission to write to Anne?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.51,1:09:56.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以寫信給安嗎？　可以\N{\rENG}- May I have permission to write Anne? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.68,1:09:59.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,你可以…\N{\rENG}You have permission...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.56,1:10:01.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,寫信給我\N{\rENG}...to write me.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.98,1:10:03.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,寫給她\N{\rENG}Oh, write her.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.36,1:10:06.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.74,1:10:09.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你，先生\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.45,1:10:13.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,牧師？\N{\rENG}Reverend?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.58,1:10:22.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,牧羊人要保護他的羊群\N{\rENG}A shepherd must tend his flock.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.00,1:10:27.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,有時要趕走野狼\N{\rENG}And, at times, fight off the wolves.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.13,1:11:10.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你確定這是合適的地方去找民兵嗎？\N{\rENG}Are you sure this is the right place to recruit for a militia?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.80,1:11:18.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,天佑吾王！\N{\rENG}God save King George!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.12,1:11:40.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想是來對地方了\N{\rENG}I think we came to the right place.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.79,1:11:49.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,有沒有賞金？　這次恐怕沒有賞金\N{\rENG}- Any bounty? - No scalp money this time, Rollins.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.84,1:11:51.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你殺了紅衫軍\N{\rENG}But you can keep 
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.30,1:11:54.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,就可以賣給我他們的槍和裝備\N{\rENG}or sell me the muskets and gear of any Redcoat you kill.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.14,1:12:08.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們在艾克華斯吊死我弟\N{\rENG}They hanged my brother down in Acworth.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.44,1:12:12.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,那些紅衫軍都該死\N{\rENG}Every damned one of them Redcoats deserves to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.36,1:12:14.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就加入我們　　我渾身殘疾…\N{\rENG}- Sign up. - With all my ailments...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.15,1:12:17.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,我撐不到前哨戰，我看還是算了\N{\rENG}...I wouldn't make it through the first skirmish. No, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.36,1:12:20.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是我的黑奴可以代我上陣\N{\rENG}But you can have my Negro. He'll fight in my stead.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.49,1:12:21.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,歐坎！過來\N{\rENG}Occam! Get over here.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.45,1:12:26.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不聰明，但很強壯\N{\rENG}Ain't overly smart. He's strong as a bull.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.17,1:12:28.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會寫字嗎？\N{\rENG}Can you write?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.25,1:12:31.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,不會\N{\rENG}No, no, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.34,1:12:33.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就畫押吧　　為什麼？\N{\rENG}- Well, then, make your mark. - Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.42,1:12:35.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我把他讓給你了\N{\rENG}I just signed him over to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.47,1:12:37.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你願意的話，我想要你畫押\N{\rENG}If you're willing, make your mark.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.43,1:12:45.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣就行了\N{\rENG}That'll do.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.98,1:12:52.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要去殺紅衫軍\N{\rENG}I'll kill me some Redcoats.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.44,1:12:54.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我相信你會\N{\rENG}I believe you would.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:55.15,1:12:56.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,你幾歲？\N{\rENG}How old are you?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.57,1:12:59.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,還不夠大，但時候會到的\N{\rENG}Not quite old enough. But his time will come.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.36,1:13:01.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·比林斯，我希望你會來\N{\rENG}John Billings. I was hoping you'd turn up.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:02.08,1:13:04.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,傳說有20名紅衫軍…\N{\rENG}There's a story going around about 20 Redcoats...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.70,1:13:07.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,被鬼殺了\N{\rENG}...got killed by a ghost or some damn thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:07.66,1:13:09.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,這鬼帶一個印第安斧頭\N{\rENG}Carried a Cherokee tomahawk.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.42,1:13:14.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,你相信鬼故事，不嫌老嗎？\N{\rENG}Aren't you a little old to be believing in ghost stories?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.65,1:14:22.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,你找到幾個？\N{\rENG}How many did you get?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.78,1:14:23.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,12個\N{\rENG}Twelve.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.57,1:14:25.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}Good.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.66,1:14:29.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要的不是這種人\N{\rENG}These men, they're not the sort we need.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.79,1:14:34.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要的正是這種人\N{\rENG}They're exactly the sort we need.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.13,1:14:38.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們以前打過這種仗\N{\rENG}They've fought this kind of war before.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.97,1:14:43.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我呢？我也是之一嗎？\N{\rENG}What about me? Am I one of that sort?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.47,1:14:45.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,當然不\N{\rENG}Hell, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.26,1:14:48.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,你這種人把恥辱帶給那種人\N{\rENG}Your sort gives that sort a bad name.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.06,1:14:57.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要求快狠准\N{\rENG}I want accuracy and precision.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.82,1:14:58.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備！\N{\rENG}Make ready!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.82,1:15:05.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄準！\N{\rENG}Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.45,1:15:11.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.54,1:15:51.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,懸賞：抓鬼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.29,1:15:51.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,懸賞：抓鬼，親愛的安：\N{\rENG}Dear Anne:
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.58,1:15:52.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,親愛的安：\N{\rENG}Dear Anne:
Dialogue: 0,1:15:52.83,1:15:54.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的軍力越來越強\N{\rENG}Our force continues to grow.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.08,1:15:59.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,只要我們奮戰不懈，其它人就會起而效尤\N{\rENG}As long as we continue to fight, others will come to fight beside us.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.75,1:16:02.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很想見你和跟你說話\N{\rENG}I long to see you and speak to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.01,1:16:05.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,也希望我能因職務之便靠近你\N{\rENG}I'm hopeful that our duties will bring me near you.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.80,1:16:10.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,在見面之前，我會時時想著你\N{\rENG}Until then, I am and will remain most affectionately yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.31,1:16:11.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列上\N{\rENG}Gabriel.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.75,1:16:39.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們投降！\N{\rENG}We surrender!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.50,1:16:42.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,不！天啊，不要！\N{\rENG}No! God, stop!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.09,1:16:44.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,看在老天的份上…\N{\rENG}For the love of God, we...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.76,1:16:47.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些人就要投降了！\N{\rENG}These men were about to surrender!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.43,1:16:50.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許吧\N{\rENG}Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.97,1:16:52.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們永遠也無從得知\N{\rENG}We will never know.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.51,1:16:53.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是謀殺！\N{\rENG}This is murder!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.10,1:16:58.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,牧師，他們是紅衫軍，他們罪該萬死\N{\rENG}Hell, reverend, they're Redcoats. They've earned it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.98,1:17:02.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們比他們好多了　　你對戰爭懂什麼？\N{\rENG}- We're better than that. - What do you know about war?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.65,1:17:04.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道為崇高目標而戰…\N{\rENG}I know the difference between fighting...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.82,1:17:06.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,回你的教堂！\N{\rENG}Go back to church!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.61,1:17:07.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,安靜！\N{\rENG}Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.74,1:17:11.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,他說得對\N{\rENG}He's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.83,1:17:15.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們要收容那些受傷及投降的英軍\N{\rENG}Quarter will be given to British wounded and any who surrender.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.62,1:17:17.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,當他們對我的妻兒坐的船開火時\N{\rENG}They gave no quarter when they fired on a ship
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.62,1:17:19.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,也沒想到要手下留情\N{\rENG} carrying my wife and daughters.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.42,1:17:24.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我在200碼外眼睜睜看著他們被燒死\N{\rENG}I watched from 200 yards off as they were burned alive.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.34,1:17:28.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很同情你，但就這樣…　去你的同情\N{\rENG}- All my sympathy, but my order stands. - Damn your sympathy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.13,1:17:30.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,你憑什麼下這種命令？\N{\rENG}Who are you to give such an order?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.22,1:17:33.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道你和你手下在維爾德尼斯堡…\N{\rENG}I know what you did to 
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.31,1:17:35.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,是怎麼對我的同胞\N{\rENG}my countrymen at Fort Wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.85,1:17:40.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們是民兵，不是正規軍\N{\rENG}We're militia. This is not regular army.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.36,1:17:43.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡的人可以自行決定去留\N{\rENG}Every man here is free to come and go as he pleases.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.07,1:17:45.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,但你們留下來的話…\N{\rENG}But while you're here...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.57,1:17:48.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,就要聽我的命令，否則軍法處置\N{\rENG}...you will obey my command or I will have you shot.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.95,1:17:56.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,該死的狗輩！　殺了它們！\N{\rENG}- Damn dogs! - Shoot the damn things!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.24,1:17:59.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,別開槍　　它們不讓任何人靠近車\N{\rENG}- Stay that pistol. - They won't let you near the wagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.38,1:18:07.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,是蘭姆酒　　難怪它們看的這麼緊\N{\rENG}- Rum, Madeira. - No wonder they were guarding it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.92,1:18:09.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,軍官的制服\N{\rENG}Officers' uniforms.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.42,1:18:11.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們猜這值多少錢？\N{\rENG}What you think all this is worth?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.76,1:18:16.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是康瓦理斯將軍的私人物品\N{\rENG}It's the personal correspondence of Lord Cornwallis.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.43,1:18:19.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是他的日記\N{\rENG}This is his journal.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.94,1:18:22.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們喝了他的酒，吃了他的狗\N{\rENG}I say we drink the wine, eat the dogs 
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.94,1:18:25.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,用這些紙來塞毛瑟槍\N{\rENG}and use the papers for musket wadding.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.27,1:18:26.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,吃他的狗？\N{\rENG}Eat the dogs?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.78,1:18:29.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,狗肉很好吃\N{\rENG}Dog is a fine meal.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.74,1:18:32.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的天啊\N{\rENG}Good heavens.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.29,1:18:47.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這裡有地圖\N{\rENG}I have some maps here for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.63,1:18:51.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,放在那裡，謝謝\N{\rENG}Put them down over there. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.43,1:18:54.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,給你一把毛瑟槍\N{\rENG}Here. A proper musket for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.97,1:18:56.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道你們怎麼樣\N{\rENG}I don't know about you,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.97,1:18:59.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我覺得不該讓黑奴拿槍\N{\rENG} but I don't like the idea giving muskets to slaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.81,1:19:04.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對自由一點概念都沒有\N{\rENG}Your sense of freedom is as pale as your skin.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.90,1:19:12.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,別聽他們的\N{\rENG}Don't listen to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:14.78,1:19:17.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,打贏這場仗很多事都會變\N{\rENG}If we win this war, a lot of things will change.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.20,1:19:19.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼會變？\N{\rENG}What will change?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.12,1:19:23.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們說這裡是新大陸，不是\N{\rENG}They call this the New World. It's not. 
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.12,1:19:25.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,這裡和舊大陸一樣\N{\rENG}It's the same as the old.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:28.42,1:19:30.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我們有機會建立新世界\N{\rENG}But we'll have a chance to build a new world.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.09,1:19:38.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,新世界中人人平等\N{\rENG}A world where all men are created equal under God.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.35,1:19:40.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,平等\N{\rENG}Equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.98,1:19:43.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,聽起來很不錯\N{\rENG}Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:44.81,1:19:47.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我剛剛看了天才的傑作\N{\rENG}I've just been in the mind of a genius.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.94,1:19:54.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,康瓦理斯對戰爭的知識豐富得令人咋舌\N{\rENG}Cornwallis knows more about warfare than we could learn in a dozen lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.07,1:19:56.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,那倒是令人振奮的好消息\N{\rENG}That's cheerful news.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.87,1:20:01.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在坎登和查理士城的勝利無懈可擊\N{\rENG}His victories at Camden and Charles Town were perfect. Perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.12,1:20:04.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,而且他心裡明白\N{\rENG}And he knows it, what's more.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.46,1:20:07.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許這就是他的弱點\N{\rENG}Perhaps that's his weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.34,1:20:09.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,長官？\N{\rENG}Sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.80,1:20:11.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,驕傲\N{\rENG}Pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.17,1:20:14.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,驕傲是弱點\N{\rENG}Pride's a weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.13,1:20:17.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還是希望他蠢一些\N{\rENG}Personally, I would prefer stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.97,1:20:21.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,驕傲就行了\N{\rENG}Pride will do.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.53,1:20:34.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,做好了\N{\rENG}Finished, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.82,1:20:36.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我把背後改緊…\N{\rENG}I've taken it in at the back...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.03,1:20:39.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,加了肩章和金邊\N{\rENG}...added wider epaulets and looped gold braiding.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.95,1:20:43.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,這簡直是馬用的毛毯　　這我就不知道了\N{\rENG}- It's a horse blanket. - I don't know, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.25,1:20:45.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,看起來很不錯\N{\rENG}It's really quite nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.91,1:20:48.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,非常不錯　　這是一條很好的馬毛毯\N{\rENG}- Very nice, my lord. - Very well. It's a nice horse blanket.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.46,1:20:53.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓上校，為什麼都等了六個星期…\N{\rENG}Colonel Tavington, why, after six weeks...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.59,1:20:56.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還在南卡參加舞會\N{\rENG}...am I still attending a ball in South Carolina...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.93,1:20:59.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,而我現在應該早就在北卡了\N{\rENG}...when I should be attending balls in North Carolina?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.80,1:21:01.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,先是我的行李被偷…\N{\rENG}First, the theft of my baggage...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.64,1:21:04.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,包括我費盡心力寫的日誌\N{\rENG}...including my memoirs, on which I spent countless hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.93,1:21:06.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,接著從這兒到查理士城\N{\rENG}Then half the bridges 
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.74,1:21:08.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,半數以上的渡口及橋樑都被燒了\N{\rENG}and ferries between here and Charles Town burned.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.94,1:21:11.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你無法對抗民兵，保護補給線…\N{\rENG}If you can't protect our supply lines against militia...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.02,1:21:15.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要怎麼對抗正規軍和法軍呢？\N{\rENG}...how do you intend doing so against the Regulars or the French?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.65,1:21:18.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們不打正規戰，我們找不到他們\N{\rENG}They won't fight like Regulars. We can't find them.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.49,1:21:20.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們是民兵\N{\rENG}Colonel, they're militia.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.62,1:21:23.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們是拿著耙子的農夫！\N{\rENG}They're farmers with pitchforks!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.75,1:21:27.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們不止是農夫\N{\rENG}They're rather more than that, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.50,1:21:30.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們是鬼影指揮官調教的\N{\rENG}Made so by their commander, this ghost.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.67,1:21:33.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,鬼，鬼，鬼\N{\rENG}Oh, ghost, ghost, ghost.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.09,1:21:36.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,那個鬼是你塑造出來的\N{\rENG}You created this ghost, colonel.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.51,1:21:39.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的階級是你幫他掛的\N{\rENG}Your brutality swelled his ranks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.55,1:21:41.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,要是沒有他們就沒有這個鬼…\N{\rENG}Without them this ghost would've disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:41.89,1:21:44.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,而我現在已到北卡了！\N{\rENG}...and I'd be in North Carolina by now!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.68,1:21:45.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要為我辯護…\N{\rENG}In my defence, my lord...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.06,1:21:48.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,夠了…！\N{\rENG}Oh, enough, enough!
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.73,1:21:52.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,虧你是個好軍人居然會怕鬼\N{\rENG}A fine soldier you are, bested by a bedtime story.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.32,1:21:56.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,把那個馬毛毯給我\N{\rENG}Give me the horse blanket.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.49,1:22:02.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,奧哈拉，我們的補給船似乎來了\N{\rENG}O'Hara, our supply ship appears to have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.20,1:22:04.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, my lord, it has.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.83,1:22:07.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我為什麼要穿這個地毯？\N{\rENG}Then why am I still wearing this rag?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.50,1:22:10.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,長官，您的禮服在船上，但是…\N{\rENG}Your replacement wardrobe is aboard ship, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.62,1:22:14.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓上校認為要先搬軍用品\N{\rENG}...Colonel Tavington thought it best to secure our arms and munitions first.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.88,1:22:16.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,弟兄們現在正在搬\N{\rENG}They are being unloaded.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.77,1:22:29.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,你穿這個顏色很好看\N{\rENG}You look good in that colour.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.35,1:22:32.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,臭死了\N{\rENG}It stinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.61,1:22:36.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,原來是死人穿的\N{\rENG}Well, it's had a dead man in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.78,1:22:38.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,那些野蠻人連你的狗都不放過？\N{\rENG}The beasts took your dogs too?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.94,1:22:40.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.20,1:22:44.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,那兩只好狗是國王送我的\N{\rENG}Fine animals. A gift from His Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:45.28,1:22:46.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,據我所知，大概已經死了\N{\rENG}Dead now, for all I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.29,1:22:49.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒有天理了嗎？\N{\rENG}Is there no decency?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.76,1:23:02.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,太棒了！是煙火\N{\rENG}Oh, fireworks. Lovely!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.50,1:23:36.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,霍華先生\N{\rENG}Mr. Howard.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.00,1:23:39.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是來看安的\N{\rENG}I've come to call on Anne.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.93,1:23:48.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是來看安的！\N{\rENG}I've come to call on Anne!
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.26,1:23:50.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,你當然是個男人\N{\rENG}Well, of course you call yourself a man.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.48,1:23:54.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親，別逗了，你聽到他說的\N{\rENG}Father, stop it. You heard him.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.36,1:23:58.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個嘛…\N{\rENG}Well...
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.07,1:24:00.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,去看她吧\N{\rENG}...call on her.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.34,1:24:27.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我快好了\N{\rENG}I'm nearly finished.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.43,1:24:31.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,別擔心，父親\N{\rENG}You needn't worry, Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.47,1:24:32.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}Yeah, I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:33.48,1:24:35.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,我覺得這布丁袋是很好的傳統\N{\rENG}Bundling bags are a wonderful tradition. 
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.82,1:24:37.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我一點都不介意\N{\rENG}I don't mind in the least.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.11,1:24:40.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要動\N{\rENG}Be still.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.23,1:24:42.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,要茶嗎？\N{\rENG}Tea?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.32,1:24:44.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,麻煩你\N{\rENG}Please.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.45,1:24:47.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\rENG}There.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:56.04,1:24:57.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,來吧，親愛的\N{\rENG}Come, dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.84,1:25:10.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}It's very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.31,1:25:15.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,你喜歡我就放心了\N{\rENG}I'm pleased that you like it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.36,1:25:25.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,彼德\N{\rENG}Peter.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.28,1:25:29.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,別擔心，我的針上工夫比我媽好\N{\rENG}Don't worry. I sew better than my mother did.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.95,1:25:34.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,希望如此\N{\rENG}I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:40.67,1:25:42.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你只是站在那裡…\N{\rENG}If you're just gonna stand there...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.00,1:25:44.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼不念出來給我們聽？\N{\rENG}...why don't you read it for us?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.84,1:25:46.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不識字\N{\rENG}I can't read.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.34,1:25:50.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會\N{\rENG}I can.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.85,1:25:54.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,請注意\N{\rENG}"Take notice.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.77,1:25:59.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,華盛頓將軍及大陸會議下令…\N{\rENG}By order of General Washington and the Continental Congress...
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.44,1:26:02.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,在獨立軍中…\N{\rENG}...all bound slaves who give minimum one year service...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.98,1:26:04.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,服役一年以上的奴隸…\N{\rENG}...in the Continental Army...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.32,1:26:07.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,將可重獲自由…\N{\rENG}...will be granted freedom...
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.03,1:26:11.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,並可得到每個月五先令的薪水\N{\rENG}...and be paid a bounty of five shillings for each month of service."
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.28,1:26:13.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你聽到了嗎？\N{\rENG}Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.87,1:26:17.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,先是要放他們自由，接下來又要付他們錢\N{\rENG}First they'll free them, then they'll pay them.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.45,1:26:19.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,只要再六個月\N{\rENG}Only another six months.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.33,1:26:24.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,你自由後要做什麼？\N{\rENG}What will you do with freedom?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.56,1:26:37.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我幫你做的\N{\rENG}I made this for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.57,1:26:55.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,好好照顧你媽\N{\rENG}Look after your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.87,1:27:02.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道嗎，彼德…\N{\rENG}You know, Peter...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.04,1:27:04.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我沒有辦法付你錢\N{\rENG}...I can't pay you for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:04.88,1:27:09.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你方便時再給\N{\rENG}Benjamin, you pay me what you can, when you can.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.51,1:27:10.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,感激不盡\N{\rENG}I'm obliged.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.26,1:27:15.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列真的很像你\N{\rENG}Gabriel sure reminds me a lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.81,1:27:19.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,不，他比較像他媽\N{\rENG}No, no, he's more like his mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.77,1:27:22.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,下士！\N{\rENG}Corporal!
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.56,1:27:25.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你慢慢來，狗兒們\N{\rENG}Take your time. Dogs.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.66,1:27:43.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生\N{\rENG}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.13,1:28:32.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,道路封閉了\N{\rENG}This road is closed.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.42,1:28:35.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,這些車輛現在正式成為獨立軍的財產\N{\rENG}These wagons now belong to the Continental Army.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.18,1:28:37.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備！\N{\rENG}Ready arms!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.44,1:28:51.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,排成兩列\N{\rENG}By twos!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.87,1:29:04.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,你和你的手下不必死，留下車子就走吧\N{\rENG}There's no need for your men to die. Leave the wagons and go.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.04,1:29:06.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是國王的公路\N{\rENG}This is the king's highway.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.12,1:29:09.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,我勸你和你的手下讓開\N{\rENG}And I advise you and your men to make way.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.80,1:29:17.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,進攻！\N{\rENG}Charge!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.93,1:29:20.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:21.35,1:29:22.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退！\N{\rENG}Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.73,1:29:31.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,保留實力！\N{\rENG}Save yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.26,1:30:00.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退！\N{\rENG}Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.90,1:30:21.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,有埋伏…！\N{\rENG}Ambush! Ambush!
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.86,1:30:56.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,我統計了一下\N{\rENG}I have the count.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:57.94,1:30:59.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,死了二十二個人\N{\rENG}22 are dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.49,1:31:02.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,十八個人受傷，二十人失蹤\N{\rENG}18 wounded and 20 are missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.16,1:31:04.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不幹了\N{\rENG}I'm through.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.50,1:31:12.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不是最後一個要走的人\N{\rENG}He won't be the last to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.83,1:31:15.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,相信我，我的同胞很快就會到\N{\rENG}Trust me. Soon my countrymen will arrive.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.29,1:31:17.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,法國軍隊…　你下地獄\N{\rENG}- The French army is... - To hell with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.46,1:31:19.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,法國軍隊下地獄\N{\rENG}And to hell with the French army.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:19.26,1:31:20.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們不需要他們\N{\rENG}We don't need them.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.59,1:31:21.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有班傑明·馬汀\N{\rENG}We got Benjamin Martin. 
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.92,1:31:24.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們知道他是怎麼對付法國人的\N{\rENG}We know what he done to the French.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.32,1:31:39.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親\N{\rENG}Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:40.24,1:31:45.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,你在維爾德尼斯堡的英勇事蹟，人人佩服\N{\rENG}Men always buy you drinks because of what happened at Fort Wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.08,1:31:49.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,陌生人都比我瞭解你\N{\rENG}Strangers know more about you than I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.79,1:31:53.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我當時的情況\N{\rENG}Tell me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.58,1:31:59.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,你出生時，你母親也問過我這個問題\N{\rENG}Your mother asked me that question around about the time you were born.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.01,1:32:04.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我當時爛醉如泥才會回答\N{\rENG}I was drunk and foolish enough to answer it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:11.35,1:32:14.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,法國人和印地安人突擊藍橋\N{\rENG}The French and the Cherokee had raided along the Blue Ridge.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.56,1:32:18.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,英國殖民到查理斯堡尋求庇護\N{\rENG}The English settlers had sought refuge at Fort Charles.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.98,1:32:22.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們抵達時那裡已經沒人了\N{\rENG}By the time we got there, the fort was abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:23.61,1:32:25.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們一周前就離開了\N{\rENG}They'd left about a week before.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.20,1:32:29.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,但是我們發現…\N{\rENG}But what we found was...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.54,1:32:33.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續說\N{\rENG}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:36.92,1:32:40.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們殺光所有的男的殖民\N{\rENG}They'd killed all the settlers, the men.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.46,1:32:44.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,女人和…\N{\rENG}With the women and...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.47,1:32:46.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,某些孩童被他們…\N{\rENG}...some of the children, they had...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.76,1:32:52.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們把他們的遺骸全埋了\N{\rENG}We buried them all, what was left of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:55.39,1:32:58.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們在維爾德尼斯堡追上他們\N{\rENG}We caught up with them at Fort Wilderness.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:01.19,1:33:02.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,??兒??綷N{\rENG}We took our time.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:05.11,1:33:07.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,把他們五馬分屍\N{\rENG}We cut them apart slowly.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.78,1:33:10.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,千刀萬剮\N{\rENG}Piece by piece.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:15.83,1:33:17.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的臉龐歷歷在目\N{\rENG}I can see their faces.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.09,1:33:23.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,耳邊仿佛回蕩著他們的尖叫\N{\rENG}I can still hear their screams.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.42,1:33:28.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們只留了兩個活口\N{\rENG}All but two. We let them live.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.14,1:33:32.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們讓那兩個人\N{\rENG}We sent the heads on a pallet...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.47,1:33:35.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,帶著那些人的項上人頭回去\N{\rENG}...with the two that lived back to Fort Ambercon.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.85,1:33:39.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,眼睛，舌頭，手指…\N{\rENG}The eyes, tongues, fingers...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.27,1:33:41.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們則裝在籃子裡\N{\rENG}...we put in baskets.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.69,1:33:44.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,送到印地安人那兒去\N{\rENG}Sent them down the Asheulot to the Cherokee.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.57,1:33:51.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,不久後，印地安人便不再與法國人合作\N{\rENG}Soon after, the Cherokee broke their treaty with the French.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.83,1:33:54.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們就是這樣平衡的\N{\rENG}That's how we justified it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.00,1:34:05.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們是…\N{\rENG}We were...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.01,1:34:08.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,英雄\N{\rENG}...heroes.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.80,1:34:12.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,那些人請你喝酒\N{\rENG}And men bought you drinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.68,1:34:21.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,我每天都在祈求上帝寬恕我\N{\rENG}Not a day goes by where I don't ask God's forgiveness for what I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.86,1:34:33.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯瑪斯是我的弟弟，也是你的兒子\N{\rENG}Thomas was my brother, as well as your son.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.20,1:34:39.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,你也許不信，但我和你一樣想要報仇\N{\rENG}You may not believe this, but I want satisfaction as much as you do.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.17,1:34:42.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,但在不影響原則下\N{\rENG}But not at the expense of our cause.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.46,1:34:46.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,仇終究是要報的\N{\rENG}There will be a time for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.01,1:34:49.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,但在那之前我會為自由奮鬥\N{\rENG}But until then, stay the course.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.59,1:34:54.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,我喝醉或發脾氣時，你媽會說這句話\N{\rENG}Your mother said that when I'd get drunk or lose my temper.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.01,1:34:57.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我挑湯瑪斯毛病時她會這麼說\N{\rENG}She'd say it to me when I picked on Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.52,1:35:04.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我好想他\N{\rENG}I miss him.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:21.42,1:35:24.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們有十八名弟兄在卡羅萊納州堡被俘\N{\rENG}The British got 18 of our men at Fort Carolina.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:24.96,1:35:28.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,除非他們說出我們下落，否則都會被吊死\N{\rENG}They'll be hung one at a time until they give up the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.94,1:35:45.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,牧師…\N{\rENG}Reverend...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.44,1:35:47.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,能幫我寫封信嗎？\N{\rENG}...can you write a letter for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.94,1:35:50.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,寫給我太太和兒子　　沒問題\N{\rENG}- To my wife and boy. - Yes, of course I will.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.65,1:35:53.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,不過，我們先來禱告\N{\rENG}But first let us pray.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.38,1:36:09.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,大人…\N{\rENG}My lord...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.80,1:36:11.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,大門外有一名騎士\N{\rENG}...there is a rider at the gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.88,1:36:14.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,一名舉白旗的平民\N{\rENG}A civilian carrying a white flag.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.01,1:36:16.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很忙\N{\rENG}I am occupied.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:17.10,1:36:19.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,他帶了兩隻狗\N{\rENG}He has a pair of dogs with him.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:20.14,1:36:22.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,是大丹狗\N{\rENG}Great Danes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.48,1:36:24.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,主啊…\N{\rENG}And dear Lord...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.69,1:36:26.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,請在這個危急的時刻，保佑我們\N{\rENG}...protect us in this, our hour of need.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.15,1:36:30.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們以聖父，聖子…\N{\rENG}This we ask in the name of the Father, the Son...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.11,1:36:32.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,和聖靈之名求您\N{\rENG}And the Holy Ghost.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.99,1:36:39.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這裡等\N{\rENG}Wait here.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.49,1:36:41.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,康瓦理斯將軍馬上來\N{\rENG}General Lord Cornwallis will be with you shortly.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.33,1:37:28.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,木星，土星，來\N{\rENG}Jupiter, Mars. Come, boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:31.13,1:37:32.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,來\N{\rENG}Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.63,1:37:39.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的乖狗狗，你們似乎沒有吃苦\N{\rENG}My good boys. My brave boys. You seem to be well fed.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.43,1:37:43.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你\N{\rENG}I thank you for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.22,1:37:45.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還不知道你的名字\N{\rENG}I'm afraid I don't know your name.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.02,1:37:50.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我是獨立軍上校，你只要知道這個就夠了\N{\rENG}I'm a colonel in the Continental Army. My rank should be sufficient for now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.11,1:37:52.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,隨你便\N{\rENG}As you wish.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.40,1:37:54.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,請坐\N{\rENG}Please be seated.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.74,1:37:55.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:57.74,1:38:01.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,請你開始說明來意吧？\N{\rENG}Would you, as the initiating officer, care to begin?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.03,1:38:04.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會的，除非你要先申報你的損失\N{\rENG}I will, unless you'd like to claim aggrieved status.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.16,1:38:07.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，我要先這麼做\N{\rENG}Yes, I would like to claim aggrieved status.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.04,1:38:09.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼，請繼續吧\N{\rENG}Very well, sir. Proceed.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.08,1:38:14.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,你手上有我的私人物品，包括衣服…\N{\rENG}You have in your possession belongings of mine including clothing...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.76,1:38:18.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,傢俱及私人日誌…\N{\rENG}...furniture, personal effects of a non-military nature...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.97,1:38:20.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望你能還我\N{\rENG}...which I'd like returned to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:21.14,1:38:23.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會儘快辦到的\N{\rENG}Indeed. I will do so as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.47,1:38:26.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:26.89,1:38:30.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我們來談談，你們在戰場上…\N{\rENG}Now we come to the matter of the specific targeting...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.19,1:38:32.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,針對我們軍官開槍的事\N{\rENG}...of officers during engagements.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.65,1:38:35.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你應該知道在文明戰爭中，戰場上軍官…\N{\rENG}You must know that in civilized warfare, officers in the field...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.03,1:38:40.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,不該表現出不合時宜的敵意\N{\rENG}...must not be accorded inappropriate levels of hostile attention.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.41,1:38:45.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,你認為怎樣才叫做不合時宜的敵意？\N{\rENG}To your mind, what are appropriate levels of hostile attention?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:45.20,1:38:47.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,想想看，要是群龍無首…\N{\rENG}Imagine the chaos that would follow...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.75,1:38:50.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,兩軍相爭時，會如何混亂\N{\rENG}...from leaderless armies having at each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.38,1:38:54.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,一定要有指揮官…\N{\rENG}There must be gentlemen in command to lead...
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.80,1:38:58.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,才能夠在必要時控制軍隊\N{\rENG}...and, where necessary, restrain their men.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.13,1:39:03.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,例如，不讓他們欺淩老弱婦孺\N{\rENG}Restrain them from, say, targeting civilians. Women, children and such.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.60,1:39:07.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,那又是另一回事了\N{\rENG}That's a separate issue.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.02,1:39:09.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,不，我認為是同一件事\N{\rENG}No. I consider them linked.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:10.64,1:39:13.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,只要你的手下攻擊平民百姓…\N{\rENG}And as long as your soldiers attack civilians...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.56,1:39:17.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就會命令我手下，開戰時屠殺你的軍官\N{\rENG}...I will order the shooting of officers at every engagement.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.19,1:39:21.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的手下都是神槍手\N{\rENG}And my men are excellent marksmen.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.91,1:39:26.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,那好\N{\rENG}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.54,1:39:30.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓我們繼續討論…　戰俘交換事宜\N{\rENG}- Now, let us move on to... - Prisoner exchange.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.67,1:39:32.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生？\N{\rENG}Sir?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.50,1:39:36.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這邊確有18名犯人，我要你放了他們\N{\rENG}You have 18 of my men. I want them back.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.68,1:39:48.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這邊的確有18名死囚\N{\rENG}I do have 18 criminals under sentence of death...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.60,1:39:51.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我絕對不會扣留戰犯\N{\rENG}...but I hold no prisoners of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.52,1:39:54.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你拒絕，你就要為你18名軍官的死負責\N{\rENG}If that's your position, 18 of your officers will have to die.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.86,1:39:56.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,19名，如果你把我一起吊死\N{\rENG}Nineteen, if you hang me with my men.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.15,1:39:58.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的軍官？\N{\rENG}My officers?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.40,1:39:59.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,先生\N{\rENG}Sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.99,1:40:09.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,在你左方的山頂的樹下\N{\rENG}Top of the ridge, to your left. Below the tree line.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.09,1:40:24.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的名字和官階？\N{\rENG}Their names and ranks?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.59,1:40:26.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們不透露姓名，有九名少尉\N{\rENG}They refused to give names. There are 9 lieutenants, 
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.59,1:40:28.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,五名上尉，三名少校…\N{\rENG}5 captains, 3 majors...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.76,1:40:30.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,和一個說我厚顏無恥的…\N{\rENG}...and one fat colonel who called me...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.52,1:40:34.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,肥上尉\N{\rENG}...a cheeky fellow.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.69,1:40:37.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,這不是紳士該有的作為\N{\rENG}This is not the conduct of a gentleman.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:37.69,1:40:40.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你軍官的作為…叫紳士作風\N{\rENG}If the conduct of your officers is the measure of a gentleman...
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.94,1:40:42.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,那我覺得，你這是天大的恭維\N{\rENG}...I'll take that as a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.03,1:40:46.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,去帶我的手下來\N{\rENG}Get my men.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.16,1:40:52.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,安排交換事宜　　大人\N{\rENG}- Arrange the exchange. - My lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.04,1:40:54.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝你\N{\rENG}Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.82,1:41:27.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,釋放囚犯！\N{\rENG}Release the prisoners!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.41,1:41:34.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,將軍，這是做什麼？　交換戰俘\N{\rENG}- What is this? - Prisoner exchange.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:34.75,1:41:36.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,他俘擄了我們十八名軍官\N{\rENG}He has 18 of our officers.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.54,1:41:38.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是誰？我看過他\N{\rENG}Who is he? I recognize him.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.92,1:41:40.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,他是民兵的指揮官\N{\rENG}He's the commander of the militia.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.05,1:41:44.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是你說的鬼　　不要動，上校！\N{\rENG}- Your ghost. - Stay that sword, colonel!
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.17,1:41:47.81,CHT,,0,0,0,,他舉著白旗前來談判，沒有敵意　是嗎？\N{\rENG}He rode in under a white flag for formal parley.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.84,1:41:49.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,這太瘋狂了\N{\rENG}This is madness.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.80,1:41:53.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果你傷害他，會害死我們的軍官\N{\rENG}If you harm him, you condemn our officers.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.52,1:41:57.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,請恕我說一句，他過去殺了不少軍官\N{\rENG}With respect, sir, he's killed as many officers in the last two months.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:58.02,1:42:02.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,他沒有敵意，所以我們不能傷害他\N{\rENG}He has shown no aggression here. Hence he cannot be touched.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.82,1:42:04.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,他沒有嗎？\N{\rENG}Has he not?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:07.95,1:42:08.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,你！\N{\rENG}You!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:09.70,1:42:12.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,原來你就是那個鬼，我記得你\N{\rENG}So you're the ghost, are you? I remember you!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.87,1:42:14.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,在農場上！那個笨小孩\N{\rENG}On that farm! That stupid little boy!
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.96,1:42:23.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,他死了嗎？\N{\rENG}Did he die?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:27.47,1:42:28.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,你知道嗎…\N{\rENG}You know...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:28.97,1:42:31.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,有時克盡職責實在很不好受\N{\rENG}...it's an ugly business, doing one's duty.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.85,1:42:33.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,但有時候…\N{\rENG}But just occasionally...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:34.64,1:42:36.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,是賞心樂事\N{\rENG}...it's a real pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:40.40,1:42:43.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,在這場戰爭結束之前，我會殺了你\N{\rENG}Before this war is over, I'm going to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.69,1:42:48.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼要等？\N{\rENG}Why wait?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.70,1:42:58.87,CHT,,0,0,0,,很快的\N{\rENG}Soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.91,1:43:33.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,出發！\N{\rENG}Move out!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.79,1:43:41.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,我還是覺得，北進太魯莽\N{\rENG}But I still think it's imperative to push north.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:44.42,1:43:46.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是我們被俘的軍官之一\N{\rENG}One of our captured officers, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.63,1:43:54.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們的無能，害我臉上無光！\N{\rENG}My reputation suffers because of your incompetence!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.14,1:43:58.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,那傢伙羞辱我！\N{\rENG}That man insults me!
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.93,1:44:02.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,這鄉巴佬還真不簡單\N{\rENG}Quite impressive for a farmer with a pitchfork, wouldn't you say?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.82,1:44:12.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要你去找他\N{\rENG}I want you to find that man.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:13.24,1:44:15.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要你把他捉來\N{\rENG}I want you to capture him.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.70,1:44:18.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,人民對他很忠心\N{\rENG}The man has the loyalty of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.41,1:44:21.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們保護他和他的家人\N{\rENG}They protect him. Protect his family.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.00,1:44:23.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,保護他手下的家人\N{\rENG}Protect the families of his men.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.04,1:44:27.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以幫你捉到他\N{\rENG}I can capture him for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.59,1:44:32.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,但這就要用到一些不太光明的手段…\N{\rENG}But to do so requires the use of tactics that are somewhat...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.72,1:44:35.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,大人之前是怎麼說的？\N{\rENG}What was the word your lordship used?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.80,1:44:39.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,好像說“殘忍”\N{\rENG}"Brutal," I think.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.15,1:44:49.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續\N{\rENG}Go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.33,1:45:01.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我準備好去做該做的事\N{\rENG}I am prepared to do what is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.20,1:45:05.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我願意為我的行為負全責…\N{\rENG}I alone will assume the full mantle of responsibility for my actions...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.87,1:45:08.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不受上級指揮…\N{\rENG}...free of the chain of command...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:08.21,1:45:10.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,不管我做什麼，你都不能怪我\N{\rENG}...rendering you blameless.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:11.09,1:45:12.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果…\N{\rENG}However...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:12.67,1:45:14.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我這麼做…\N{\rENG}...if I do this...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.68,1:45:18.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們兩個都知道，我永遠無法載譽歸國\N{\rENG}...you and I both know that I can never return to England with honour.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.89,1:45:25.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我將會有何下場？\N{\rENG}What, I wonder, is to become of me?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.24,1:45:36.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,當這裡的戰爭結束之後…\N{\rENG}When this war is over here in the Colonies...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.66,1:45:38.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,新興貴族…\N{\rENG}...the new aristocracy...
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.53,1:45:42.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,將會是地主\N{\rENG}...will be landowners.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.67,1:45:52.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我俄亥俄州的事\N{\rENG}Tell me about Ohio.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:57.93,1:45:59.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓開\N{\rENG}Make way.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:00.22,1:46:01.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,稍息\N{\rENG}As you were.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:04.60,1:46:08.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,威爾金，離維克菲爾七英哩處…\N{\rENG}Wilkins. A plantation seven miles from Wakefield, on the Santee...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.90,1:46:13.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,山提河東岸的黑沼澤，是什麼人住的？\N{\rENG}...east of Black Swamp. Who lived there?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.15,1:46:14.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,班傑明·馬汀\N{\rENG}Benjamin Martin.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:14.86,1:46:16.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,他就是我們說的鬼\N{\rENG}He's the ghost.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.32,1:46:18.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對他知道多少？\N{\rENG}What do you know about him?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.95,1:46:22.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,無所不知，?疫B他幾號鞋都知道\N{\rENG}Hell, everything. I could tell you the size of his boot.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.45,1:46:27.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,他有家人嗎？他把孩子藏在哪裡？\N{\rENG}Does he have family? Where would he hide his children?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:36.39,1:46:39.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的小姨子有一個農莊\N{\rENG}His wife's sister has a plantation.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.52,1:46:41.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,不遠\N{\rENG}It's not far.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.93,1:47:18.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,夏綠蒂阿姨，醒醒，有人來了！\N{\rENG}Aunt Charlotte! Wake up, someone's coming!
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.65,1:47:25.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,去叫孩子們\N{\rENG}Get the boys.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:27.73,1:47:30.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,瑪格莉特，快來\N{\rENG}Margaret, come quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:30.57,1:47:33.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們走　　孩子們，來吧\N{\rENG}- Let's go. - Boys, come.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.95,1:47:34.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,快！\N{\rENG}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.62,1:47:41.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟著我\N{\rENG}Stay close.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:47.13,1:47:48.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,走這邊，從窗臺下出去\N{\rENG}This way.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.02,1:48:06.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟著我\N{\rENG}Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:09.69,1:48:12.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們下樓到廚房\N{\rENG}We'll go downstairs to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.37,1:48:20.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,瑪格莉特，快！從這下麵！快！\N{\rENG}Margaret, quick! Get down there! Fast!
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.55,1:48:34.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,山繆，快下來！\N{\rENG}Samuel, get down there fast!
Dialogue: 0,1:49:31.94,1:49:33.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,在下面，那裡\N{\rENG}Beneath the sill. There.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.49,1:49:38.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,房子裡沒有人\N{\rENG}There's no one in the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.24,1:49:39.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們一定沒走遠\N{\rENG}They can't be far.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:40.12,1:49:42.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,去樹林裡找找\N{\rENG}Search the outbuildings and the woods, quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:20.24,1:50:22.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備放火燒房子\N{\rENG}Prepare to fire the house.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:22.91,1:50:24.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,快走\N{\rENG}Go.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:44.01,1:50:45.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是他們家裡的奴隸\N{\rENG}This one's head of the house slaves.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:51.19,1:50:52.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們躲在哪裡？\N{\rENG}Where are they hiding?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.61,1:50:58.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,繼續找，他們一定在附近！\N{\rENG}Keep looking! They're here somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.82,1:51:06.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列　　父親呢？\N{\rENG}- Gabriel. - Where's Father?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.79,1:51:08.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,放火燒房子！\N{\rENG}Torch the house!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.14,1:51:27.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,上馬！\N{\rENG}To horse!
Dialogue: 0,1:51:34.52,1:51:36.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,跟我來，不要緊的\N{\rENG}Come on! It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.44,1:51:38.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,蘇珊，過來\N{\rENG}Susan, come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.53,1:51:48.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,夏綠蒂！\N{\rENG}Charlotte!
Dialogue: 0,1:52:04.55,1:52:07.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們不會放棄找我們的\N{\rENG}They won't stop looking for us.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.72,1:52:11.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們會帶你們去安全的地方\N{\rENG}You'll be safe where we're taking you.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:12.73,1:52:15.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親說在那裡藏身最適合了\N{\rENG}Father said it was a perfect place to hide.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.90,1:52:19.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,他還好嗎？\N{\rENG}How is he?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.65,1:52:26.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不知道，我是他的兒子\N{\rENG}I don't know. I'm his son.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:26.70,1:52:28.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親呢？\N{\rENG}Where is Father?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.12,1:52:31.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,幾個月前開始說話\N{\rENG}Speaking for months now.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:31.91,1:52:33.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,幾個月前開始說話\N{\rENG}Speaking for months.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:33.71,1:52:35.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,他到哪裡去了？\N{\rENG}Why did he go?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.71,1:52:39.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,他不要那些人找到你們\N{\rENG}He didn't want those mean men to find you, 
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.71,1:52:41.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以他引他們離開\N{\rENG}so he led them away.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.80,1:52:44.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,他會儘快回來看你們\N{\rENG}He'll come see you as soon as he can.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.47,1:52:47.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不管，我恨他\N{\rENG}I don't care. I hate him.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:48.85,1:52:50.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,蘇珊，你不恨他\N{\rENG}Susan, you don't hate him.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:50.72,1:52:54.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我恨他，我希望他永遠不回來\N{\rENG}I hate him, and I hope he never comes back.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.09,1:53:29.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,是孩子們\N{\rENG}It's the children.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:31.01,1:53:32.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,艾比佳！\N{\rENG}Abigale!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.93,1:53:35.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,你還活著！\N{\rENG}You're alive!
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.61,1:53:49.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道不多，但你可以跟我一起\N{\rENG}I know it's not much, but you can stay here with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:08.51,1:54:10.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,很美\N{\rENG}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.51,1:54:13.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:25.40,1:54:29.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說話了，蘇珊跟你說話了？\N{\rENG}She spoke. Susan talked to you?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:29.45,1:54:31.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,整句\N{\rENG}In full sentences.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:31.32,1:54:33.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,好像她一直都可以說話\N{\rENG}As if she'd been speaking all along.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:36.33,1:54:38.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,可惡，我居然不在場\N{\rENG}Damn, I wasn't there for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:39.50,1:54:40.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說什麼？\N{\rENG}What did she say?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:43.17,1:54:44.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,她說…\N{\rENG}She said...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.46,1:54:49.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,她很愛你也很想你…\N{\rENG}...that she loves you and misses you...
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.01,1:54:54.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,她也瞭??銥槭?N不能來陪她\N{\rENG}...but understands why you can't be with her.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:55.68,1:54:57.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,天啊，真的嗎？\N{\rENG}My Lord, she said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.18,1:54:58.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,真不可思議\N{\rENG}Isn't that something?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:03.44,1:55:06.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓有我們的名單，在燒我們的房子…\N{\rENG}Tavington has a list of our men. He's burning our homes...
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.52,1:55:08.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,若有不從，格殺勿論\N{\rENG}...killing whomever resists.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:09.03,1:55:13.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,在哪裡？　他燒了山提河岸的七棟房子\N{\rENG}- Where? - Seven homes along the Santee so far.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:00.50,1:56:02.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰\N{\rENG}John.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:11.17,1:56:13.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在不是報仇的時候\N{\rENG}John, this is not a time for vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:14.38,1:56:16.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,是哀悼的時候\N{\rENG}This is a time for mourning.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:21.60,1:56:23.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰\N{\rENG}John.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:32.11,1:56:33.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,不！\N{\rENG}No!
Dialogue: 0,1:56:51.42,1:56:53.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,去照顧你們的家人\N{\rENG}Attend to your families.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:55.55,1:56:57.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,所有的人都放一周假\N{\rENG}One week furlough for all men.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:58.68,1:57:00.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果收假時，不回來的人\N{\rENG}Any man who does not return
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.68,1:57:02.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,不會當你是懦夫臨陣脫逃\N{\rENG} will not be thought a coward or uncommitted.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:19.07,1:57:20.41,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親！\N{\rENG}Father!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:21.83,1:57:23.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸！\N{\rENG}Papa!
Dialogue: 0,1:57:29.58,1:57:31.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,天啊，他們長得好大，你給他們吃什麼？\N{\rENG}They're huge. What have you been feeding them?
Dialogue: 0,1:57:31.92,1:57:35.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們有爸爸的優良血統\N{\rENG}They're from good stock on their father's side.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.72,1:57:45.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,蘇珊？\N{\rENG}Susan?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:25.18,1:58:28.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我看到了，在那裡，快看，父親！\N{\rENG}I see it. There it is. Look. Look, Father.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:30.65,1:58:32.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,我抓到了…！\N{\rENG}I got it! I got it!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:32.98,1:58:34.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,你抓到了\N{\rENG}You got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:34.82,1:58:36.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我抓到了！\N{\rENG}I got it!
Dialogue: 0,1:58:36.40,1:58:37.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,小心　　我抓到了\N{\rENG}- Careful. - I caught it.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:37.69,1:58:40.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,魚都在這裡　　我們去抓\N{\rENG}- All the fish are over here. - Let's get them.
Dialogue: 0,1:58:47.20,1:58:49.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親，什麼事情改變了你？\N{\rENG}Father, what changed you?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:51.50,1:58:53.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,你確定我變了嗎？\N{\rENG}Are you sure I have?
Dialogue: 0,1:58:53.59,1:58:56.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的，你變了\N{\rENG}Yes. You changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:04.01,1:59:05.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,很簡單\N{\rENG}That's simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:06.10,1:59:07.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,是你媽媽\N{\rENG}It was your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:12.56,1:59:15.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,女人對男人會有很奇怪的影響力\N{\rENG}A woman can have a strange effect on a man.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:16.78,1:59:18.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,曾經…\N{\rENG}There were times...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:19.07,1:59:21.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,在你媽身邊，我連呼吸都有困難\N{\rENG}...I had trouble breathing around your mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:22.53,1:59:24.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我瞭解你的感受\N{\rENG}I know the feeling.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:26.28,1:59:27.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說過…\N{\rENG}You once said...
Dialogue: 0,1:59:30.87,1:59:33.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,等我成家之後自然會明白\N{\rENG}...when I had a family of my own, I'd understand.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:37.38,1:59:38.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說得對\N{\rENG}You were right.
Dialogue: 0,1:59:41.51,1:59:43.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想告訴我什麼？\N{\rENG}You're trying to tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:00.28,2:00:01.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,要吃蘋果嗎？　謝謝\N{\rENG}- Apple? - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:08.66,2:00:09.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,恭喜\N{\rENG}Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:10.08,2:00:11.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,安·派翠莎·霍華…\N{\rENG}Anne Patricia Howard...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:12.04,2:00:16.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,你願意嫁給此人為妻？\N{\rENG}...will you have this man to be your husband to live in marriage?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:16.50,2:00:19.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會愛他，照顧他，榮顯他…\N{\rENG}Will you love, comfort and honour him...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:19.30,2:00:21.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,至死方休？\N{\rENG}...for so long as you both shall live?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:22.09,2:00:23.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,我願意\N{\rENG}I will.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:23.88,2:00:27.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列·艾德華·馬汀，你願娶此女為妻…\N{\rENG}Gabriel Edward Martin, will you have this woman to be your wife...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:27.30,2:00:29.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,共同生活嗎？\N{\rENG}...to live together in the covenant of marriage?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:30.35,2:00:34.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,你會愛她，安慰她，榮顯她至死方休嗎？\N{\rENG}Will you love, comfort and honour her as long as you both shall live?
Dialogue: 0,2:00:34.73,2:00:35.77,CHT,,0,0,0,,我願意\N{\rENG}I will.
Dialogue: 0,2:00:36.02,2:00:38.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,我依上帝…\N{\rENG}Then by the power vested in me by our mutual faith...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:39.11,2:00:40.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,賦予我的權力…\N{\rENG}...in the Lord, our God...
Dialogue: 0,2:00:41.23,2:00:44.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,宣佈你們二人結為夫妻\N{\rENG}...I now pronounce you man and wife.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:11.68,2:01:13.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,抱歉沒有早點告訴你\N{\rENG}I'm sorry we didn't give you more warning.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:14.14,2:01:15.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒關係\N{\rENG}It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:15.77,2:01:17.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,我有東西要給你\N{\rENG}I have something for you.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:19.94,2:01:21.65,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是佳百列他媽媽的\N{\rENG}It belonged to Gabriel's mother.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:21.90,2:01:23.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,好漂亮\N{\rENG}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:24.61,2:01:25.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓我來\N{\rENG}Allow me.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:27.20,2:01:28.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是北極星\N{\rENG}It's the North Star.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:29.24,2:01:32.83,CHT,,0,0,0,,是天空中唯一不會動的星星\N{\rENG}That's the only star in the sky that never moves.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:33.12,2:01:36.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,它永遠不會動搖\N{\rENG}It's constant, unwavering.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:36.67,2:01:38.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,為人指引方向\N{\rENG}A guide.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:41.46,2:01:43.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很榮幸\N{\rENG}I'd be honoured.
Dialogue: 0,2:01:48.34,2:01:49.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,我可以嗎？\N{\rENG}May I?
Dialogue: 0,2:01:49.59,2:01:51.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,你堅持的話　　我堅持\N{\rENG}- If you must. - I must.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:07.95,2:02:09.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,我能坐在你身邊嗎？\N{\rENG}May I sit with you?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:09.61,2:02:11.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,這是個自由的國家\N{\rENG}It's a free country.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:12.45,2:02:13.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,至少以後會是\N{\rENG}Or at least it will be.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:26.13,2:02:28.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不是我姐\N{\rENG}I'm not my sister.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:29.26,2:02:30.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know that.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:31.51,2:02:33.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,是嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:34.39,2:02:35.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:36.98,2:02:38.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}Very well, then.
Dialogue: 0,2:02:42.98,2:02:44.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼樣？\N{\rENG}Well?
Dialogue: 0,2:02:45.90,2:02:47.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,什麼怎麼樣？\N{\rENG}Well what?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:09.38,2:03:11.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們很快就在潘布克見\N{\rENG}I'll see you in Pembroke soon.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:11.43,2:03:13.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,那不夠快\N{\rENG}Not soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:13.85,2:03:15.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,我現在要靠你了…\N{\rENG}I'm counting on you to make sure...
Dialogue: 0,2:03:15.97,2:03:17.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道　　知道什麼？\N{\rENG}- I know. - What?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:17.72,2:03:22.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,幫我禱告，照顧每個人　　一點都沒錯\N{\rENG}- Say my prayers, take care of everyone. - Couldn't have said it better.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:26.07,2:03:27.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見\N{\rENG}Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:27.69,2:03:28.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見\N{\rENG}Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:49.13,2:03:50.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見，蘇珊\N{\rENG}Goodbye, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,2:03:52.84,2:03:54.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,再見？\N{\rENG}Goodbye?
Dialogue: 0,2:03:57.26,2:03:58.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,我只要你說一句話就好了\N{\rENG}Just one word, that's all I want.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:08.15,2:04:09.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}All right.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:36.93,2:04:38.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸！\N{\rENG}Papa!
Dialogue: 0,2:04:41.02,2:04:43.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,爸爸，別走！我什麼都說\N{\rENG}Papa, don't go! I'll say anything.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:48.11,2:04:49.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,求求你，爸爸\N{\rENG}Please, Papa.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:51.94,2:04:53.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要我說什麼，我就說什麼\N{\rENG}I'll say anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,2:04:54.20,2:04:57.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴我你要我說什麼，我什麼都說\N{\rENG}Tell me what you want me to say. I'll say anything.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:00.20,2:05:03.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,我保證，爸爸，不要走\N{\rENG}I promise, Papa. Please don't go.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:04.12,2:05:05.46,CHT,,0,0,0,,我保證\N{\rENG}I promise.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:06.33,2:05:07.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會回來的\N{\rENG}I'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:08.63,2:05:10.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會回來的，你相信我嗎？\N{\rENG}I'll come back. You believe me?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:14.09,2:05:16.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,你讓我非常快樂\N{\rENG}You know, you make me very happy.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:52.13,2:05:53.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,只有我們三個？\N{\rENG}Just the three of us?
Dialogue: 0,2:05:54.34,2:05:56.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,約翰·藍斯金來過\N{\rENG}John Raskin did come by earlier.
Dialogue: 0,2:05:57.59,2:05:59.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,他看了看就走了\N{\rENG}He looked around, then he left.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:00.60,2:06:01.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,那就四個人了\N{\rENG}He would've made four.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:02.43,2:06:04.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,四個人會比較好\N{\rENG}Four would have been better.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:39.47,2:06:42.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,我再撐兩個月就滿一年了\N{\rENG}I got another two months to go before I get to twelve months.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:48.23,2:06:49.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,上校\N{\rENG}Colonel.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:50.44,2:06:51.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,牧師\N{\rENG}Reverend.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:55.23,2:06:56.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,相信法國人\N{\rENG}Trust the French.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:57.40,2:06:58.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,是，相信法國人\N{\rENG}Yes, trust the French.
Dialogue: 0,2:06:58.90,2:07:02.49,CHT,,0,0,0,,還有什麼其它機會能殺紅衫軍？\N{\rENG}Where else do I get the opportunity to kill a few Redcoats?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:03.03,2:07:07.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許趁你不注意時，能殺幾個受傷的\N{\rENG}Perhaps a few wounded ones when you are not looking.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:32.85,2:07:34.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,大家都到教堂去集合\N{\rENG}Everyone must gather at the church.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:35.57,2:07:36.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,威爾金先生？\N{\rENG}Mr. Wilkins?
Dialogue: 0,2:07:38.07,2:07:41.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓上校有話對村民說\N{\rENG}Colonel Tavington wishes to address the whole village.
Dialogue: 0,2:07:58.84,2:08:03.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,本鎮人民幫助班傑明·馬汀和他的叛黨\N{\rENG}This town has given aid to Benjamin Martin and his rebels.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:03.55,2:08:05.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,我要知道他的下落\N{\rENG}I wish to know his whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:06.85,2:08:08.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,所以…\N{\rENG}So...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:08.35,2:08:10.35,CHT,,0,0,0,,只要有人說出他的下落…\N{\rENG}...anyone who comes forward...
Dialogue: 0,2:08:10.68,2:08:12.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,我就饒了他的叛國罪\N{\rENG}...may be forgiven their treason.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:18.53,2:08:19.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rENG}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:19.78,2:08:23.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,別說我沒給過你們機會　　等等！\N{\rENG}- You had your chance. - Wait!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:23.41,2:08:25.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,他給過他們補給品　　安靜！\N{\rENG}- This man gives them supplies. - Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:25.82,2:08:27.98,CHT,,0,0,0,,他帶他們去黑沼澤　　他說謊！\N{\rENG}- He brings them to Black Swamp. - Liar!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:27.99,2:08:30.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在西班牙教會旁的沼澤\N{\rENG}In the marsh, by the old Spanish mission.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:31.08,2:08:32.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,這個人嗎？\N{\rENG}This man here?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:32.66,2:08:34.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,是的　　你說黑沼澤？\N{\rENG}- Yes. - The Black Swamp, you say?
Dialogue: 0,2:08:35.01,2:08:38.01,CHT,,0,0,0,,就在西班牙教會旁的沼澤\N{\rENG}By the old Spanish mission.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:39.09,2:08:40.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:46.69,2:08:48.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,把門關上\N{\rENG}Shut the doors.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:50.44,2:08:52.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說會原諒我們\N{\rENG}But you said we'd be forgiven.
Dialogue: 0,2:08:52.61,2:08:53.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,你是會被原諒！\N{\rENG}And indeed you may!
Dialogue: 0,2:08:56.61,2:08:58.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,那是你和上帝之間的事\N{\rENG}That's between you and God.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:05.50,2:09:06.71,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們一定要堅強\N{\rENG}Be strong. We must.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:08.79,2:09:10.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們準備放火燒城了\N{\rENG}I'll fire the town on your orders.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:10.67,2:09:11.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,燒城？\N{\rENG}The town?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:12.79,2:09:14.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,把教堂放火燒了\N{\rENG}Burn the church.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:16.88,2:09:18.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,這樣做太不磊落\N{\rENG}There's no honour in this.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:20.97,2:09:23.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,你不是說，任何背叛英國的人…\N{\rENG}Didn't you say all those who stand against England...
Dialogue: 0,2:09:23.97,2:09:26.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,都罪該萬死嗎？\N{\rENG}...deserve to die a traitor's death?
Dialogue: 0,2:09:29.14,2:09:31.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,放火燒教堂\N{\rENG}Burn the church, captain.
Dialogue: 0,2:09:43.95,2:09:44.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,把火把拿來\N{\rENG}Give me the torch.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:28.04,2:10:30.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,榮耀是來自結果，而不是手段\N{\rENG}The honour is found in the end, not the means.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:31.96,2:10:33.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,這一切會被忘記的\N{\rENG}This will be forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,2:10:34.29,2:10:35.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,波頓\N{\rENG}Bordon.
Dialogue: 0,2:12:15.19,2:12:16.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,安！\N{\rENG}Anne!
Dialogue: 0,2:12:20.65,2:12:22.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,霍爾夫人？\N{\rENG}Mrs. Howard?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:26.49,2:12:28.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,大家都到哪兒去了？\N{\rENG}Where is everybody?
Dialogue: 0,2:12:33.16,2:12:35.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們不在這裡\N{\rENG}They're not here.
Dialogue: 0,2:13:43.52,2:13:45.07,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列走了\N{\rENG}Gabriel's gone.
Dialogue: 0,2:14:30.36,2:14:32.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,快去拿武器…！\N{\rENG}To arms! To arms!
Dialogue: 0,2:18:52.37,2:18:53.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親\N{\rENG}Father.
Dialogue: 0,2:18:55.09,2:18:57.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要講話…\N{\rENG}Just don't talk. Don't talk.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:03.72,2:19:04.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,父親\N{\rENG}Father.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:05.22,2:19:07.56,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉　　安靜\N{\rENG}- I'm sorry. - Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:07.76,2:19:09.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會照顧你的，你不會有事的\N{\rENG}I'll take care of you. You'll be all right.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:12.94,2:19:16.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,湯瑪斯的事我很抱歉\N{\rENG}I'm sorry about Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:22.45,2:19:24.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,兒子，那不是你的錯\N{\rENG}Oh, son, that wasn't your fault.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:28.87,2:19:30.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我的錯\N{\rENG}That was mine.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:34.42,2:19:37.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,忍著點，你不會有事的\N{\rENG}Hold on. You're gonna be all right.
Dialogue: 0,2:19:40.34,2:19:43.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要死，佳百列\N{\rENG}Don't go. Gabriel, don't.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:12.33,2:20:14.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,上帝，幫幫我…\N{\rENG}Oh, God help me. God help me.
Dialogue: 0,2:20:48.70,2:20:49.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,他在哪裡？\N{\rENG}Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,2:20:57.83,2:20:59.84,CHT,,0,0,0,,我來幫你埋了他\N{\rENG}I'll help you bury him.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:02.00,2:21:03.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我自己來\N{\rENG}I'll bury him.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:06.59,2:21:09.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我太太懷孕了\N{\rENG}My wife in Alexandria is with child.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:10.85,2:21:12.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,是我們的第一胎\N{\rENG}My first.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:13.18,2:21:15.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,我為那孩子作戰\N{\rENG}I fight for that child.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:17.64,2:21:20.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,班傑明，沒有人能取代你兒子\N{\rENG}Benjamin, nothing will replace your sons.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:21.52,2:21:26.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,但如果你跟我們來，他們就不會白死\N{\rENG}But if you come with us, you can justify their sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:27.53,2:21:28.95,CHT,,0,0,0,,為什麼？\N{\rENG}Why?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:30.70,2:21:34.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,為何你們會覺得他們不會白死\N{\rENG}Why do men feel they can justify death?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:41.29,2:21:43.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,是傲慢還是…？\N{\rENG}Is it arrogance or?
Dialogue: 0,2:21:47.88,2:21:49.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我長久以來的恐懼…\N{\rENG}I have long feared...
Dialogue: 0,2:21:51.60,2:21:56.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,就是我舊日的罪愆…會回來糾纏我\N{\rENG}...that my sins would return to visit me.
Dialogue: 0,2:21:58.10,2:22:00.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,代價之高，我無法承受\N{\rENG}And the cost is more than I can bear.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:02.06,2:22:05.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,班傑明，我們有機會\N{\rENG}Benjamin, we have a chance.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:06.44,2:22:09.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,葛林和丹摩根從維吉尼亞來了\N{\rENG}Greene and Dan Morgan are down from Virginia.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:12.37,2:22:15.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我們打贏下一戰，就勝利在望了\N{\rENG}If we win this next battle, victory in the war is within our grasp.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:16.04,2:22:17.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,那麼，去吧\N{\rENG}Go, then.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:17.41,2:22:19.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,去追求你們的勝利\N{\rENG}Seek your victory.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:22.58,2:22:25.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不重要　　你錯了，班傑明\N{\rENG}- I'm small issue to it. - You're wrong, Benjamin.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:26.42,2:22:28.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,你對你的手下…\N{\rENG}You matter to your men...
Dialogue: 0,2:22:29.93,2:22:31.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,和對其他人都很重要\N{\rENG}...and to others as well.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:32.26,2:22:34.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的勝利…\N{\rENG}Your victories...
Dialogue: 0,2:22:34.26,2:22:36.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,和失去的…\N{\rENG}...and your losses...
Dialogue: 0,2:22:37.43,2:22:39.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,大家都感同身受\N{\rENG}...are shared by more than you know.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:40.77,2:22:42.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,和我們一起吧\N{\rENG}Stay with us.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:43.44,2:22:45.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,為自由而戰\N{\rENG}Stay the course.
Dialogue: 0,2:22:55.16,2:22:57.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,我已經為我的理由奮鬥過了\N{\rENG}I have run my course.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:17.31,2:23:19.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,你的手下跟我們走\N{\rENG}You men will be leaving with us.
Dialogue: 0,2:23:22.64,2:23:24.19,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備出發\N{\rENG}Prepare the baggage.
Dialogue: 0,2:24:28.71,2:24:29.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,尚\N{\rENG}Jean.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:28.27,2:25:30.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,你明天不能上，上校\N{\rENG}You will be missed tomorrow, colonel.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:30.73,2:25:33.11,CHT,,0,0,0,,不能上？　你的傷\N{\rENG}- Missed, my lord? - Your wound.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:34.36,2:25:36.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒關係的\N{\rENG}It's nothing, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:37.07,2:25:40.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,我隨時準備效命\N{\rENG}I am, as ever, ready to serve.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:40.32,2:25:42.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,很好\N{\rENG}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:42.37,2:25:44.79,CHT,,0,0,0,,你最好可以\N{\rENG}Make sure you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:45.33,2:25:49.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,馬上就能取得最大一場勝利，別讓我失望\N{\rENG}I stand on the eve of the greatest victory of my career. Don't fail me.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:49.71,2:25:54.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的努力，不能把你弄來這裡\N{\rENG}My efforts in no small measure have brought you here.
Dialogue: 0,2:25:54.67,2:25:56.30,CHT,,0,0,0,,我賜給你一次機會\N{\rENG}I grant you that small measure...
Dialogue: 0,2:25:56.47,2:25:59.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,雖然你沒能把鬼帶給我\N{\rENG}...in spite of your failure to deliver the ghost to me.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:00.97,2:26:02.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,從現在開始\N{\rENG}Thus far.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:03.85,2:26:06.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,我不會再容忍你由於…\N{\rENG}I will not tolerate a premature charge...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:07.06,2:26:10.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,渴求榮耀而產生的擅斷\N{\rENG}...born of your eagerness for glory.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:11.31,2:26:14.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,等候我的命令\N{\rENG}Wait for my order.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:15.07,2:26:19.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,不然我就得拋棄所有俄亥俄州的希望\N{\rENG}Or you may abandon any hope of Ohio.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:22.87,2:26:26.04,CHT,,0,0,0,,明天的戰役，將會改變整場戰事\N{\rENG}Tomorrow's battle can alter the course of the war.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:26.25,2:26:29.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,葛林將軍，我們究竟會遭遇何種情況？\N{\rENG}General Greene, what exactly is the task before us?
Dialogue: 0,2:26:29.41,2:26:32.54,CHT,,0,0,0,,各位，我們被康瓦理斯包圍了\N{\rENG}Gentlemen, Cornwallis has us cornered.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:33.21,2:26:34.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,他的人數比我們多\N{\rENG}Not only does he outnumber us...
Dialogue: 0,2:26:35.13,2:26:38.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的手下幾乎全是民兵\N{\rENG}...but nearly half of our force is militia.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:39.51,2:26:41.80,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們靠不住\N{\rENG}Unreliable, at best.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:42.14,2:26:43.97,CHT,,0,0,0,,對不起，長官\N{\rENG}Excuse me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:45.68,2:26:47.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你低估了我們的民兵\N{\rENG}You underestimate our militia.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:49.64,2:26:51.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,你們都一樣\N{\rENG}All of you do.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:51.81,2:26:54.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們看過民兵防線接二連三地被擊潰\N{\rENG}We've seen our militia lines break time and again.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:54.69,2:26:56.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,克比斯灣，普林斯頓\N{\rENG}Kips Bay, Princeton.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:56.53,2:26:58.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,但英國人也這麼想\N{\rENG}But the British have seen that too.
Dialogue: 0,2:26:59.65,2:27:03.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,康瓦理斯的信中，完全看不起民兵\N{\rENG}Cornwallis' own letters bear out that he has no respect for the militia.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:04.20,2:27:06.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,你有何建議？\N{\rENG}What are you suggesting, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,2:27:08.00,2:27:09.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,我建議我們利用這點\N{\rENG}I'm suggesting we use that.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:17.09,2:27:21.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道你們已經犧牲了很多\N{\rENG}I know you men have sacrificed a lot so far.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:21.30,2:27:24.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,但我只要求你們…\N{\rENG}But all I'm asking is that you...
Dialogue: 0,2:27:24.89,2:27:28.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,讓前兩排的民兵開兩槍\N{\rENG}...let the front line of the militia fire two shots tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:30.23,2:27:33.60,CHT,,0,0,0,,發射兩輪子彈期間，可能會發生很多事\N{\rENG}A lot can happen in the time it takes to fire two shots.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:33.60,2:27:36.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,特別是在對抗英國正規軍時\N{\rENG}Especially against British Regulars.
Dialogue: 0,2:27:37.07,2:27:40.82,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯，所以我才不叫你們開三槍\N{\rENG}Indeed. That's why I'm not asking you to fire three.
Dialogue: 0,2:28:37.96,2:28:40.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我死的話，至少死得體面\N{\rENG}If I die, I will die well dressed.
Dialogue: 0,2:29:26.55,2:29:27.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:29:31.51,2:29:34.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,大隊！　停！\N{\rENG}- Battalion! - Company, halt!
Dialogue: 0,2:29:51.49,2:29:52.58,CHT,,0,0,0,,哈利…\N{\rENG}Harry...
Dialogue: 0,2:29:53.54,2:29:55.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,麻煩把這給我的孩子們\N{\rENG}...will you give this to my children?
Dialogue: 0,2:30:06.05,2:30:07.22,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:16.43,2:30:18.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在是十月\N{\rENG}It's October now.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:20.77,2:30:21.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,我知道\N{\rENG}I know.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:22.94,2:30:24.86,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在已經超過十二個月了\N{\rENG}It's more than 12 months.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:25.32,2:30:26.61,CHT,,0,0,0,,你自由了\N{\rENG}You're a free man.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:27.78,2:30:30.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,我自願留下來\N{\rENG}I'm here now on my own accord.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:34.41,2:30:36.50,CHT,,0,0,0,,你願留下來我很榮幸\N{\rENG}I'm honoured to have you with us.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:38.83,2:30:40.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,真的很榮幸\N{\rENG}Honoured.
Dialogue: 0,2:30:41.71,2:30:44.25,CHT,,0,0,0,,舉槍！\N{\rENG}Shoulder arms!
Dialogue: 0,2:30:49.97,2:30:51.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,前進…\N{\rENG}Forward...
Dialogue: 0,2:30:52.39,2:30:53.68,CHT,,0,0,0,,齊步走！\N{\rENG}...march!
Dialogue: 0,2:30:58.64,2:31:00.44,CHT,,0,0,0,,你女兒幾歲了？\N{\rENG}How old were your daughters?
Dialogue: 0,2:31:02.52,2:31:05.02,CHT,,0,0,0,,維爾莉特十二，寶琳十歲\N{\rENG}Violette was 12 and Pauline, 10.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:06.19,2:31:08.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,他們的眼睛都是綠的\N{\rENG}They had green eyes.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:09.44,2:31:11.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,她們一定很可愛\N{\rENG}I'm sure they were lovely.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:12.86,2:31:14.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯\N{\rENG}Yes, they were.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:26.38,2:31:27.59,CHT,,0,0,0,,大隊！　注意！\N{\rENG}- Battalion! - Company!
Dialogue: 0,2:31:27.96,2:31:29.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,齊步走！\N{\rENG}March!
Dialogue: 0,2:31:31.34,2:31:32.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄準！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:31:35.39,2:31:36.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,除非我在做夢…\N{\rENG}Unless I'm dreaming...
Dialogue: 0,2:31:37.35,2:31:42.18,CHT,,0,0,0,,我好像看到…他們隊伍中央居然是民兵\N{\rENG}...I believe I see militia forming at their centre.
Dialogue: 0,2:31:55.74,2:31:58.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,大隊！停！\N{\rENG}Battalion, halt!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:16.22,2:32:18.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,第一排向前！\N{\rENG}Dress ranks!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:26.86,2:32:28.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備！\N{\rENG}Make ready!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:40.08,2:32:41.91,CHT,,0,0,0,,大隊！\N{\rENG}Battalion!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:42.12,2:32:43.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,停！\N{\rENG}Halt!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:46.25,2:32:47.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄準！\N{\rENG}Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,2:32:50.92,2:32:51.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:03.06,2:33:04.14,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:25.16,2:33:26.42,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要走散！\N{\rENG}Hold the line!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:32.38,2:33:35.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,準備進攻！　我們還沒有接到命令！\N{\rENG}- Prepare to charge! - We haven't been given that order.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:35.88,2:33:37.26,CHT,,0,0,0,,進攻！\N{\rENG}Charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:38.43,2:33:39.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,進攻！\N{\rENG}Charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:43.06,2:33:44.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,塔維頓\N{\rENG}Tavington.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:44.64,2:33:46.85,CHT,,0,0,0,,他真該死！該死！\N{\rENG}Damn him! Damn that man!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:48.73,2:33:50.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄準！\N{\rENG}Make ready.
Dialogue: 0,2:33:50.81,2:33:52.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:53.19,2:33:54.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:55.53,2:33:56.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,2:33:57.78,2:34:00.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！ 撤退！\N{\rENG}Fire! Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,2:34:06.12,2:34:10.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,上刺刀，看看鹿死誰手\N{\rENG}Bayonet charge. We'll see who takes the glory from this field.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:10.54,2:34:12.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,進攻！\N{\rENG}Charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:34:32.02,2:34:33.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,恭喜你，大人\N{\rENG}Congratulations, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:33.65,2:34:35.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫步兵儲備軍過來\N{\rENG}Infantry reserve into the centre.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:35.32,2:34:36.78,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們已經佔領了此地\N{\rENG}But you've taken the field.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:36.99,2:34:38.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,現在我們要打垮他們的士氣\N{\rENG}Now we'll take their spirits.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:38.45,2:34:41.57,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫我們的士兵去擊潰他們\N{\rENG}Send the battalion over that hill and crush them.
Dialogue: 0,2:34:41.82,2:34:43.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰爭今天就要結束\N{\rENG}It ends today.
Dialogue: 0,2:35:06.56,2:35:07.64,CHT,,0,0,0,,暫停進攻！\N{\rENG}Hold the charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:08.68,2:35:09.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:09.98,2:35:12.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,暫停進攻！\N{\rENG}Hold the charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:15.98,2:35:17.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:22.95,2:35:24.03,CHT,,0,0,0,,瞄準！\N{\rENG}Take aim!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:25.70,2:35:27.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:35.59,2:35:37.13,CHT,,0,0,0,,進攻！\N{\rENG}Charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:35:43.97,2:35:45.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,上刺刀！\N{\rENG}Charge bayonets!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:14.75,2:36:15.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等！不要走散！\N{\rENG}Halt!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:17.13,2:36:18.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等！不要走散！\N{\rENG}Hold! Dress your ranks!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:21.17,2:36:22.38,CHT,,0,0,0,,開火！\N{\rENG}Fire!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:25.84,2:36:27.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,進攻！\N{\rENG}Charge!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:51.08,2:36:52.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退！\N{\rENG}Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,2:36:58.00,2:36:59.09,CHT,,0,0,0,,上校！\N{\rENG}Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:01.00,2:37:02.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們的軍隊要瓦解了！\N{\rENG}The line is faltering!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:03.88,2:37:06.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退…\N{\rENG}Retreat! Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:14.27,2:37:15.69,CHT,,0,0,0,,等等！\N{\rENG}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:16.48,2:37:18.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,不要撤退！\N{\rENG}No retreat!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:22.03,2:37:24.24,CHT,,0,0,0,,保持隊形！\N{\rENG}Hold the line!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:25.86,2:37:27.99,CHT,,0,0,0,,保持隊形！\N{\rENG}Hold the line!
Dialogue: 0,2:37:39.71,2:37:42.75,CHT,,0,0,0,,推進！\N{\rENG}Push forward, men!
Dialogue: 0,2:38:32.22,2:38:34.51,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫炮兵到中間集合！\N{\rENG}Artillery, concentrate on the centre.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:49.74,2:38:51.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,如果我們重新整隊朝右前進\N{\rENG}If we reform and wheel right, 
Dialogue: 0,2:38:51.74,2:38:53.74,CHT,,0,0,0,,也許能逼他們撤退\N{\rENG}we may be able to turn their flank.
Dialogue: 0,2:38:53.74,2:38:55.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,你想得美，將軍\N{\rENG}You dream, general.
Dialogue: 0,2:41:58.18,2:42:01.55,CHT,,0,0,0,,拜託你在戰爭結束之前殺了我\N{\rENG}Kill me before the war is over, will you?
Dialogue: 0,2:42:02.39,2:42:05.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,看來你…\N{\rENG}It appears you are not...
Dialogue: 0,2:42:05.27,2:42:07.48,CHT,,0,0,0,,還是不如我\N{\rENG}...the better man.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:21.16,2:42:22.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,你說得對\N{\rENG}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:27.00,2:42:29.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,我的兒子比你好多了\N{\rENG}My sons were better men.
Dialogue: 0,2:42:56.86,2:42:58.32,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫他們撤退\N{\rENG}Sound the retreat.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:01.87,2:43:03.33,CHT,,0,0,0,,叫他們…\N{\rENG}Sound...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:04.45,2:43:05.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,撤退\N{\rENG}...retreat.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:23.68,2:43:24.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,親愛的夏綠蒂\N{\rENG}Dear Charlotte:
Dialogue: 0,2:43:25.47,2:43:27.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰事已經改觀\N{\rENG}The war has turned.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:27.43,2:43:30.94,CHT,,0,0,0,,康瓦理斯將軍帶著手下逃向北方\N{\rENG}General Cornwallis took flight with his army and moved north.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:31.10,2:43:34.31,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們持續與英軍交戰在未來數月間…\N{\rENG}We continued to engage the British, and in the following months...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:34.40,2:43:37.73,CHT,,0,0,0,,康瓦理斯會被困在維吉尼亞州約克鎮\N{\rENG}...Cornwallis entrenched himself at Yorktown, Virginia.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:38.61,2:43:42.16,CHT,,0,0,0,,約克鎮，1781年{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:43:39.36,2:43:41.53,CHT,,0,0,0,,喬治·華盛頓悄悄地突圍到北方\N{\rENG}Washington escaped from the north...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:41.70,2:43:45.28,CHT,,0,0,0,,包圍了康瓦理斯，他無法撤退至海上\N{\rENG}...and surrounded Cornwallis, who could not retreat to the seas.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:45.28,2:43:48.70,CHT,,0,0,0,,因為我們期待已久的朋友終於抵達\N{\rENG}It was blocked off by our long-lost friends...
Dialogue: 0,2:43:48.75,2:43:51.08,CHT,,0,0,0,,擋住他的去路\N{\rENG}...who had finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:55.75,2:43:57.17,CHT,,0,0,0,,法國萬歲\N{\rENG}Vive la France.
Dialogue: 0,2:43:59.88,2:44:01.47,CHT,,0,0,0,,自由萬歲\N{\rENG}Vive la liberte.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:13.65,2:44:15.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,大人，我求你\N{\rENG}My lord, I beseech you.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:16.11,2:44:18.40,CHT,,0,0,0,,你一定要下令投降\N{\rENG}You must order the surrender.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:19.23,2:44:23.06,CHT,,0,0,0,,怎麼可能會變成這樣？他們只是雜牌軍\N{\rENG}How could it come to this? An army of rabble.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:23.07,2:44:24.45,CHT,,0,0,0,,莊稼漢\N{\rENG}Peasants.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:26.53,2:44:28.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,一切都會不同\N{\rENG}Everything will change.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:32.12,2:44:34.12,CHT,,0,0,0,,一切都不同了\N{\rENG}Everything has changed.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:34.88,2:44:36.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,雖然他終於還是投降了…\N{\rENG}Though he eventually surrendered...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:37.17,2:44:39.63,CHT,,0,0,0,,但康瓦理斯無臉見人…\N{\rENG}...Cornwallis himself hid in shame...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:39.84,2:44:43.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,派他的手下前來投降\N{\rENG}...appointing his subordinate to relinquish his sword.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:44.64,2:44:47.76,CHT,,0,0,0,,戰爭就要結束，民兵團即將解散…\N{\rENG}With the war ending, and our militia disbanding...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:47.97,2:44:50.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我回顧我們所失去的…\N{\rENG}...I take measure of what we have lost...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:50.85,2:44:52.39,CHT,,0,0,0,,及我們得到的\N{\rENG}...and what we have won.
Dialogue: 0,2:44:53.56,2:44:58.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,我希望這麼多人的犧牲…\N{\rENG}My hope and prayer is that the sacrifices borne by so many...
Dialogue: 0,2:44:58.52,2:45:02.36,CHT,,0,0,0,,能夠讓我們的新國家誕生\N{\rENG}...will spawn and fulfil the promise of our new nation.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:03.78,2:45:06.10,CHT,,0,0,0,,告訴孩子們，尤其要告訴蘇珊\N{\rENG}Tell the children, and especially Susan,
Dialogue: 0,2:45:06.10,2:45:07.90,CHT,,0,0,0,,我會遵守諾言…\N{\rENG}that I will keep my promise...
Dialogue: 0,2:45:07.91,2:45:11.37,CHT,,0,0,0,,我很快就會回到你們身邊\N{\rENG}...as I will be returning to you all soon.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:17.63,2:45:19.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,你要去哪裡？\N{\rENG}Where will you go now?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:20.09,2:45:22.34,CHT,,0,0,0,,回家，從頭開始\N{\rENG}Home. Start over.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:22.59,2:45:24.93,CHT,,0,0,0,,你太太就快生了，對吧？\N{\rENG}Your wife's expecting a child, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:25.13,2:45:27.89,CHT,,0,0,0,,她三周前生了個兒子\N{\rENG}She gave birth to a son three weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:29.05,2:45:30.43,CHT,,0,0,0,,你幫他取什麼名字？\N{\rENG}What'd you name him?
Dialogue: 0,2:45:32.52,2:45:34.52,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們叫他佳百列\N{\rENG}We named him Gabriel.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:40.11,2:45:41.15,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝，哈利\N{\rENG}Thank you, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:48.37,2:45:51.29,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列是個適合農夫的名字\N{\rENG}Gabriel is a good name for a farmer.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:51.58,2:45:54.00,CHT,,0,0,0,,沒錯\N{\rENG}It is. It is.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:54.54,2:45:55.66,CHT,,0,0,0,,尚\N{\rENG}Jean.
Dialogue: 0,2:45:55.91,2:45:56.96,CHT,,0,0,0,,班\N{\rENG}Ben.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:04.36,2:47:07.27,CHT,,0,0,0,,佳百列說如果我們打贏的話…\N{\rENG}Gabriel said if we won the war...
Dialogue: 0,2:47:07.44,2:47:10.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我們會建立一個全新的世界\N{\rENG}...we could build a whole new world.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:10.24,2:47:13.20,CHT,,0,0,0,,我想我們就從這裡開始…\N{\rENG}Just figured we'd get started right here...
Dialogue: 0,2:47:14.62,2:47:17.23,CHT,,0,0,0,,從你們的家開始\N{\rENG}...with your home.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:20.33,2:47:22.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,好主意\N{\rENG}Sounds good.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:25.17,2:47:26.21,CHT,,0,0,0,,謝謝\N{\rENG}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,2:47:31.01,2:47:32.05,CHT,,0,0,0,,夫人\N{\rENG}Ma'am.
